title: salmon mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Drain.
Take out bones and flake salmon.
Heat soup and cream cheese over low heat until cheese is dissolved.
Add softened gelatin and stir until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in well-greased fish mold and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Unmold on bed of endive or lettuce.
Serve with toast or crackers.
Garnish with lemon.

title: pizza in biscuits
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add catsup, Ragu, sugar, vinegar, oregano and Worcestershire sauce.
Divide biscuits and roll out.
Put in muffin tins that are greased.
Add meat mixture into the tins.
Sprinkle cheeses on top.
Bake following directions on biscuit container.
Makes 20.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender with celery and onion.
Debone and cut into bite size pieces.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients through the onion and mix.
Add water and buttermilk and stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients. Drop by rounded teaspoons into hot oil (375°) and fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 30 to 40 hush puppies.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Place sauerkraut in strainer and rinse well under cold running water.
Thoroughly drain off all liquid and place kraut in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until thoroughly blended. Spoon salad into jars or plastic containers and cover.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: dessert
directions: Put pineapple in bottom of 13 x 9 baking pan.
Then put cherry pie filling over the pineapple.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over fruit.
Then place patties of butter over the cake mix.
Lay pecan halves over the top.
Bake at 350° until the cake mixture is lightly browned (or at 325° in glass baking dish).

title: marvelous stew
directions: Mix
all ingredients well.
Put into buttered casserole and cover tightly.
Bake at 250° for 4 1/2 hours.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or muffin tins. Freeze overnight.

title: hidden valley sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry with paper towels and combine with cheeses, salad dressing, olives and peppers.

title: macaroni cheeseburger casserole
directions: Boil macaroni as directed.
Brown meat and saute onion; drain. Add soup, milk and mustard.
Lay cheese, in chunks, on top to melt.
Put macaroni in 2 casseroles and add sauce.
Stir.
(One can be frozen for later).
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff(low-fat)
directions: Saute beef cubes in pan sprayed with nonstick coating (Pam). Add 1 cup water, wine, garlic and soup mix. Bring to a boil and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Add mushrooms and tarragon; simmer 10 to 15 minutes until mushrooms are tender. Thicken with flour or cornstarch.
Remove from heat. Add sour cream. Stir until blended. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cook macaroni for 5 to 8 minutes in boiling salt water, until just tender.
Drain.
Stir butter into noodles.
Add 2 cups cheese, milk, salt and pepper; pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes, until cheese is well set.
Sprinkle on remaining 1/4 cup cheese and crumbs or chips, then broil 1 minute, until brown on top.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: green vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a well-greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Coconut may be mixed into pie mixture or sprinkled on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Yields 1 pie.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, then stir in pecans. Pour into pastry shell. Bake in 400° oven 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer. Outer edge of filling should be set, center slightly soft.

title: 7-up or sprite salad
directions: In pan, dissolve the 2 boxes of jello in 2 cups water.
Add the 2 cups of 7-Up or Sprite.
Heat on stove until liquid turns from froth to clear.
Pour mixture into glass dish at least 12 x 9 x 2-inch and place into refrigerator to jell.
When jelled mixture thickens, add the sliced bananas and marshmallows.
Stir together and leave in fridge to jell.

title: cloud nine cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pack in a 13 x 9-inch pan for crust.

title: chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: Bring water to a boil. Stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes or until all water is absorbed. Meanwhile, cook and stir in hot oil until lightly browned. Stir in soup, milk, mustard and cheese; add broccoli and pimento. Bring to a full boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes. Pour over rice.

title: barbecue sauce for poultry or pork
directions: Boil vinegar and spices slowly for 5 minutes.
Add oil and return to boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add beaten egg and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: wine cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Take about a tablespoon.
Roll between your palms of your hand and you can make any design you wish.
Wrap around your finger.
Make a circle or make just a straight little fingers.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed and let cool.
Beat pudding mix, milk, and Cool Whip until smooth.
Fold in pineapple.
Frost cake with Cool Whip mixture and chill until you are ready to serve.

title: diet punch
directions: Mix both packs of Kool-Aid in 1 gallon water.
Pour 1/2 in another gallon container.
Pour 1/2 of each juice and ginger ale in each gallon container.
Makes 2 gallons punch.

title: easy cookies
directions: Roll in powdered sugar. Bake at 325° to 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: country french chicken
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and brown chicken on both sides.
Stir in soup mix, blended with water and juice.
Arrange 1 lemon slice on each piece of chicken.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened and chicken is done.
Serve over rice.
Low-fat!
Contains 7 grams fat and 211 calories.

title: zesty cracker snacks
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat and sausage.
Cube Velveeta cheese and combine with meat.
Spread on toast.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: old fashion bran muffin
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar in a large bowl, with mixer.
Add eggs.
Blend in milk, Bran Buds mixture and remaining 2 cups Bran Buds.
Add all dry ingredients; stir until moist.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs.
Add ground orange and raisins.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour milk or buttermilk.
Add walnuts.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place drained beans in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with water chestnuts, soup, cheese and almonds.
Heat until bubbly at 350°.
Add French fried onions last 5 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Place beans, scallions, chili powder, garlic and cumin in medium bowl. Mash with masher.
Cut tortillas in half.
Line bottom of dish with 4 halves, placing 2 on the long side with round edges to center. Spread half of bean mix on tortillas.
Top with 4 more halves. Spoon corn on top.
Sprinkle half of cheese and all chillies.
Top with last tortilla halves.
Spread remaining bean mix.
Spoon tomatoes and liquid over beans.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake 40 minutes until cheese is bubbly.
Top with sour cream and scallions.
Fat content:
12 grams.

title: grandma's potato cake
directions: Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk (set aside).
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and potatoes; mix well. Mix flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and cocoa together.
Stir all of the ingredients together and mix well.
Add lemon and vanilla extract. Add pecans.
Stir well.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap chicken breast with Carson dry beef, then wrap bacon around that and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup, sour cream and water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes covered and 30 minutes uncovered.
Serve over rice.

title: pineapple orange salad
directions: Drain juice from fruits into measuring cup. Add enough water to equal 3 cups. Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add fruit juice and sour cream to jello. Beat by hand until sour cream is dissolved.
Place in refrigerator to chill, about 45 minutes. Remove from refrigerator and stir in fruit. Return to refrigerator.
Serve when jello is firm.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, flour and cheese.
Pour in baking dish.
Combine oleo and cracker crumbs.
Spread over top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Goes great with ham.

title: buttermilk angelfood cake
directions: 1. Mix all ingredients together.
2. Grease and flour angelfood pan.
3. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Cook macaroni, following directions on package.
Rinse in cold water; drain.

title: baked eggplant parmigiana
directions: Blend butter and Parmesan.
Spread on both sides of eggplant slices.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange slices in single layer on a Pam-sprayed baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 15 or 20 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; add taco seasoning mix.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add chips just before serving.
Toss well.

title: pear cake
directions: Combine together sugar and oil; add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Set aside.
Sift flour with cinnamon, salt and soda 3 times, then add to creamed mixture. Add mixture.
Add vanilla; mix.
Add coconut, dates, pears and pecans, stirring by hand (batter will be thick).
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until cake tests done with a wooden pick inserted in center. Cool on rack or until cake shrinks from sides of pan.
Remove from pan to complete cooling.
Yields 16 servings.

title: koulourakia
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add the baking powder, vanilla, baking soda and 3 cups flour.
Stir in the last 3 cups flour.
Roll into pencil-like shapes.
Twist into rope shapes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned on greased cookie sheet.

title: beef and vegetable soup
directions: Cook the ground beef and onions, drain, stir in sauce mix, water, bay leaf, salt, pepper and tomatoes (with Liquid).
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occassionally. Add the noodles and veg, cover and cook for a further 10 minutes.

title: carrots with butter
directions: Bring the water, sugar and salt to a boil in a saucepan and add the carrots.
Cover.
Boil slowly until carrots start to get tender.
Uncover the pan and cook longer, until the liquid has evaporated.
Season with additional salt and pepper.
Add butter and parsley.
Stir and serve.

title: south seas chicken and bananas
directions: In food processor, blend lemon juice, condensed milk, coconut and cardamon until smooth.
Pour into a bowl.
Dip bananas into milk mixture.
Roll in cornflakes and set aside.
Dip chicken into remaining milk mixture.
Roll in the remaining cornflakes and place in 2 greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Drizzle with 1/2 cup of the melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Arrange bananas over the chicken; drizzle with butter.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until chicken juices run clear.
Garnish with kiwi or star fruit, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: autumn pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together pumpkin, milk, egg, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and hot water.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: christmas cheese
directions: Grate cheese and garlic; add cream cheese, salt and milk to soften.
Add olives and nuts.
Form into a roll and roll in paprika.
Keep in wax paper in the refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.

title: mick's potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes as instructed on box.
When completed, add the cheese and bacon bits.
Stir until cheese is melted and bacon bits are evenly distributed.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Crush Ritz and mix with margarine. Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: salmon tempura with spinach saute
directions: Skin salmon; cut into bite size.
Shred carrot.
Break egg into bowl.
Mix it.
In a bowl, mix carrot, egg, flour and 1 teaspoon of oil.
Dip salmon into flour mix.
Deep fry salmon.

title: low-fat e.z.  mix up salad
directions: In large bowl, mix cottage cheese, drained pineapple, dry jello mix, drained mandarin oranges and Cool Whip.
Mix all together and place in container in refrigerator overnight before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: parsley french toast
directions: Slice bread into slices.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread generously over bread.

title: apple nut log(christmas eve party delights)
directions: Combine cream cheese, apple juice and nutmeg in mixing bowl; blend until smooth.
Pour lemon juice over chopped apples.
Add apples and 3/4 cup of pecans to cheese mixture; blend well.
Shape into one 6-inch log and roll in remaining chopped nuts.
Wrap in plastic.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with wheat toast.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Serve with raw vegetables, crackers or rye bread.
Makes 1 quart.

title: salmon squares
directions: Make white sauce, blending melted Crisco, flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook until thick; cool.
Add 1 egg, 1 cup cracker crumbs, salmon, onion and lemon juice.
Mix well; pack into loaf pan.
Chill.
Cut slices from loaf.
dip in remaining crumbs (you may need a little more cracker crumbs), then 1 egg, beaten with 2 teaspoons water, and again in crumbs.
Fry in Crisco until lightly or nicely browned on all sides.

title: salad pizza
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, roll out crescents and press edges together.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pineapple cream cheese ball
directions: In medium size bowl, beat cheese with fork until soft.
Add pineapple, 1/2 amount of pecans, pepper, onion and salt.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Can also be frozen for use later.

title: appetizer
directions: Melt all ingredients together.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: sugar-free cake
directions: Combine and cook raisins and water until water is absorbed. Cool; combine eggs, applesauce, oil, vanilla and sweetener.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to egg mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: easy party chicken
directions: Place clean and dried chicken in greased baking dish, skin side up.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Pour salad dressing over top.
Drop spoonfuls of preserves over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Take cover off during the last 15 minutes to brown.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy cole slaw(pennsylvania dutch style)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate for several hours and serve. Gets better after it marinates.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Boil whole head of cauliflower for 10 minutes; drain.
Place on glass pie plate.
Brush with butter.
Frost with the mixture of mayonnaise, mustard and grated cheese.
Sprinkle with parsley. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken wings in honey sauce
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Cut wings into sections you may discard the tips.
Sprinkle wings with salt and pepper.
Place on broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from broiler for 20 minutes, ten minutes on each side.
Transfer to crock pot.
For the sauce, combine honey, soy sauce, ketchup, oil and garlic in bowl.
Pour over chicken wings in the Crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 5 hours.
Garnish with sesame seeds as desired.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain, peel and put potatoes in mixing bowl.
Add sugar, eggs, milk, salt, vanilla and margarine. Beat with mixer until smooth. Put mixture into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with topping and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: russian hot pot
directions: Put water and bouillon cubes in a 4-quart Dutch oven (heavy covered pot) and bring to boil over medium heat.
Meanwhile, scrub potatoes.
Cut in 1/2-inch chunks (3 1/2 cups) and add to pot. Increase heat to high.
Remove core, then cut cabbage into 1/2-inch chunks (6 cups).
Peel and quarter the onion.
Add to pot with cabbage.
Add tomatoes, breaking them up with your fingers.
Add the beef, crumbling it up as it goes into pot.
Let contents of pot boil about 30 seconds.
Stir to mix well.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serve in soup plates.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Stir together first four ingredients and spread evenly in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes, stirring every five minutes.
Sprinkle 3/4 of the crumbs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add flour mix to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla; chill dough.
Roll on pastry cloth. Cut with 2-inch cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: christmas bread
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, fruits, nuts and spices. In another bowl, combine eggs, butter and rum extract and add wet to dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon batter into greased pans; bake at 350° until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove to rack to cool completely.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In Pam sprayed casserole, spread cabbage.
Pour on milk and dot with margarine.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer or until crumbs are browned.

title: world's best macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Melt margarine in a large saucepan.
Add onion and let saute for 3 minutes, using low heat. Do not let brown.
Add flour; blend well.
Add hot milk and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add cooked macaroni that has been well drained.
This makes 1 large or 2 (1 1/2-quart) casseroles.
This freezes well.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients while potatoes are still warm.
Add milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar, fold into potato mix.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes then lower to 350° and bake until set.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and Mountain Dew.
Bake 3 layers, using cake mix directions for heat and time.

title: catalina salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil with rotary beater.
Gradually beat in oil.
Refrigerate.

title: classic 7-up pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine butter, shortening, 3 cups sugar and extracts in a large bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour and salt.
Add alternately with 1 cup of the 7-Up, beating well after each addition.
Spoon into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.

title: icebox salad
directions: Make jello.
Let set until starts to jell.
Mash in cream cheese until not lumpy.
Add drained pineapple, whipped cream and nuts.
Set overnight.
Decorate with split cherries.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix nuts, 1 cup coconut and dates.
Add 1 egg; beat remaining egg with vanilla.
Add to the first mixture.
Mix in melted butter and brown sugar.
Roll one teaspoon of dough in remaining coconut and drop onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs; mix dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake 30 minutes in moderately hot oven at 350°.

title: lentils and rice(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Rinse the rice in a strainer under cold running water, then soak in cold water for 30 minutes and drain in a strainer.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in mini bits.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Season roast with the listed seasoning.
Wrap in 2 layers of foil.
Put in crock-pot and cook on low for 12 to 16 hours.

title: banana nut pie
directions: Boil milk (unopened) for 3 hours.
Pour half of cooked milk into pie shell.
Add layer of pecans, then sliced bananas.
Pour other half of milk over bananas.
Top with Dream Whip and decorate with cherries and pecans.

title: honey cookies(this is a sweet recipe.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
(Raisins, chocolate chips and nuts are optional.)
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: banana loaf cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes or until tooth pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add vegetables and saute.
Add dry seasonings.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Add can of chicken.
Heat thoroughly.
Place in thawed pie shell; top with second pie shell. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: taco salad
directions: In large bowl, chop lettuce.
Add grated cheese.
Pour in salad dressing.
Let sit while cooking meat.
Brown meat and onion.
Pour off grease.
Add hot chili beans.
Crush Doritos. Mix all together and serve.

title: texas hash
directions: Saut (cook slow with butter) the onions, green pepper and ground beef until vegetables are tender. Drain well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Spoon into a 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done. Yields 8 servings.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Blend cheese and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix pineapple, strawberries, bananas and nuts.
Blend in softened Cool Whip; fold into cream cheese mixture.
Freeze in mold or 9 x 13-inch dish. Remove from freezer 25 to 30 minutes before serving.
You can keep this frozen for months, just take out what you want.

title: frozen oreo dessert
directions: Combine Oreos and butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan as first layer.
For second layer, spread softened ice cream.
Spread hot fudge for third layer.
Sprinkle nuts for fourth layer.
For fifth layer, spread whipped cream.
Add crumbled cookies for the sixth layer.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat over low temperature until well blended. Do not boil. Great on chicken.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark.
Mix
other ingredients.
Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheets or waxed paper.
Makes a lot.

title: cheese blitz
directions: Roll each piece of bread with a rolling pin.
Mix together cream cheese, egg, almond and sugar.
Spread on each slice, then roll up.
Pour some of the melted margarine onto a small plate. Roll each slice in the margarine and then in the cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Cut into halves or thirds.
Can be frozen for later use. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 50 to 75, depending on how they are cut.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over steaks which have been pierced with a fork several times. Marinate 12 to 24
hours in refrigerator.
Turn meat several times and spoon marinade over. Broil or charcoal grill steaks to desired degree of doneness. Excellent marinade also for chicken, pork, etc.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: In greased square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch), stir together the first 5 ingredients.
Mix in the next 3 ingredients until smooth. Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter (do not stir!).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream!!

title: mapled apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Toss apples, syrup and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon in a baking dish.
Set aside.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread in 9-inch baking pan. Combine seasonings with pizza sauce.
Spread on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle hamburg on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Add Mozzarella.
Bake for 7 to 10 more minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let cool about 10 minutes.
Serve with corn chips or dip chips.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Add 1/4 teaspoon soda to mashed bananas and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, oil, eggs and vanilla altogether.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake in loaf pans at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until done.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix the salsa and cream cheese; dip with chips.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Cool.
When cool, crumb the cake into tiny pieces.
Place 1/2 of the crumbs in a punch bowl. Add 3 bananas, sliced, next layer is 1/2 the pudding.
Add next 1/2 of the pineapple (drained) and now 1 can strawberry pie filling, 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Now add the 1 cup pecans.
Repeat all the layers again.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: crab bisque(serves 4)
directions: Mix ingredients together and heat to serving temperature.
Add 2 tablespoons sherry.
Pour into individual crocks.
Top each with French bread slices and Swiss cheese.
Place under broiler until the cheese bubbles.

title: light and fruity pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: cheese fondue
directions: In large bowl, place cheese, flour and seasonings.
Toss to combine.
In a saucepan, heat wine to simmering.
Add cheese mixture gradually, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted and mixture thickens.
Transfer to fondue pot.
Set to low heat.
Serve with bread cubes.

title: spring surprise pudding
directions: Put
rhubarb
and
water
in
saucepan	and
cook until tender, about
or 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Simmer 10 minutes
longer.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Cream
together
shortening and sugar.
Add grated orange rind and egg
and beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla to milk and add
to
creamed
mixture alternately with flour mixture. Stir until smooth.
Pour batter into greased 8 x 8-inch square pan. Pour
bubbling
hot rhubarb sauce over the batter.	Bake at 350° for
about	45
minutes.
Serve with whipped topping. Serves 6.

title: aunt annabell's apricot cake
directions: Combine cake mix and gelatin. Add oil, then one egg at a time, beating well in between.
Add nectar and extract.
Stir to mix. Bake in a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cover the bottom of the crust with Swiss cheese.
Put on spinach, mushrooms and ham.
Stir the eggs with the cream; pour over the ham, mushrooms and spinach.
Sprinkle paprika; dot with butter.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pink fluff
directions: Boil crushed pineapple and sugar slowly for 5 minutes.
Add strawberry gelatin (dry).
Mix until dissolved; cool.
Beat cream cheese with milk until fluffy.
Fold in cold pineapple and gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.
Fills a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares to serve as a dessert, or on a lettuce leaf as a salad.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer all ingredients in a nice punch bowl or a nice bowl, ending with Cool Whip.

title: mrs. friemel's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Cook on hot griddle or in electric skillet.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, well beaten.
Add sifted flour, salt and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: deb's peanut butter frosting
directions: Melt chips with 1/2 cup cream.
Let cool to room temperature. Whip the rest of the cream.
Fold in peanut butter mixture.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Chop shrimp, onion and green pepper in fine pieces.

title: mandarin orange jello
directions: Mix orange jello, sugar, boiling water and orange juice.
Let set partially.
Add the mandarin oranges and pineapple to the jello.
Let set until solid.
While jello is setting, mix the vanilla pudding with 1 cup milk.
Let set.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Spread onto set jello mixture and chill.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until brown.

title: spiced orange mold
directions: Drain oranges; reserve syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 3/4 cups.
In a saucepan, mix syrup, salt and spices.
Cover and simmer ten minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand, covered, ten minutes longer.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Combine crumbs, salt, pepper and butter. Sprinkle 1/3 of mixture in a buttered casserole and cover with 1/2 the oysters.
Repeat layers.
Add Worcestershire to milk and pour over top.
Sprinkle 1/3 crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine ground beef, 1 1/3 cups instant mashed potato flakes, 1 cup milk, egg, ketchup, onion, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Spread into 9-inch pie plate.
Cook at Medium-high 6 /12 to 7 1/2 minutes; drain.
Arrange 2 slices cheese on top.
Let stand, loosely covered, 7 minutes.
Meanwhile, in medium glass bowl, combine water, butter, remaining milk, salt and pepper. Cook at Medium-high 5 to 6 minutes.
Add remaining instant mashed potato flakes and cheese, diced and stir until potatoes are fluffy.
Spread over "cheeseburger".
Cook at Medium-high 2 to 3 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chicken deluxe
directions: Crisp
bacon in skillet.
Put washed chicken in shallow oven dish.
Wash
and dice leek.
Put leek and bacon on top of chicken; cover
dish.
Bake
in
oven until chicken is cooked (about an hour).
Bake
at
Add
half
and half in the final stages of cooking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seaburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in hamburger rolls.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fantastic fudge
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa together.
Mix well.
Melt butter and cheese in double boiler.
Blend the margarine and cheese into sugar mixture completely.
Mix in the vanilla and nuts.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan; allow to stand.
Cut into squares.

title: holiday pound cake
directions: Toss candied fruits and nuts with 1/4 cup flour.
Set aside. Blend cream cheese, margarine, sugar and flavorings.
Add eggs, one at a time. Gradually add remaining flour mixed with baking powder. Fold in candied fruits and 1/2 cup nuts.
Heavily coat whole pan with shortening.

Do not flour. Sprinkle other 1/2 cup nuts on bottom of pan and pour batter on top of them. Bake in a 9-inch tube pan at 325° for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cake does not rise very high. Can also be baked in a Bundt pan.

title: taco bean dip
directions: In a medium bowl stir together bean dip and taco seasoning mix. Spread mixture on a 10-inch tray or pie plate.
Sprinkle with onions.
Stir together salad dressing (or mayo) and sour cream. Then spread on top of onions.
Top with olives.
Cover and chill several hours.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove from broth, cool, debone and cut into pieces.
Strain broth, cool and remove fat.
Cook noodles in 1 quart chicken broth.
Make sauce by melting butter and adding bell pepper, onion and flour.
Blend well.
Add milk and 2 cups broth.
Cook until sauce is thick. Stir in cheese and cook over low heat until it melts.
Combine chicken, noodles, mushrooms and cheese sauce.
Add salt and pepper.
Place in a 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Mix together and form into patties.
Broil or grill them.

title: easy rocky road
directions: Place chocolate chips, butter and shortening in large microwaveproof bowl.
Microwave at Medium for 5 to 7 minutes or until chips are softened and mixture is melted and smooth when stirred.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Blend well.
Spread evenly in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cover.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: cauliflower cheese soup
directions: Combine cauliflower, carrots, celery and broth in large saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Put pork chops in a large baking pan.
Add 1 slice tomato, 1 slice onion and 1 slice bell pepper, stacked on each pork chop.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Empty beets and their liquid into a small saucepan.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and cloves.
Heat just until sugar dissolves. Cool to room temperature.
Place eggs in a medium-sized bowl or jar.
Pour in the beet mixture and add just enough water so liquid covers eggs.
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator 2 to 3 days, stirring now and then or inverting the jar several times to redden evenly.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon and egg in a large mixing bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until blended. Spoon into 1 greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; set aside. Combine apples, 1/2 cup sugar, the flour and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon or cloves in a 1-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High until apples are tender and sauce is bubbly (3 to 4 minutes).

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet; cook until beef is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off grease; add salt, pepper, catsup and tomato sauce.
Heat.
Turn into an 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle on grated cheese.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown meat; add vegetables.
Cook vegetables until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and simmer 20 minutes.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Take crackers and break into four parts and lay them on a cookie sheet.
Mix rest of ingredients in a small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook for about 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over graham crackers and bake in oven about 7 minutes.
It will be bubbling.
Remove from cookie sheet and place on wax paper until cool.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well. Spread on bottom of square baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, dash of salt and pepper.
Cover with crumbled bacon.
Spread sour cream to seal; sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hearty breakfast
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine eggs, milk, shortening and pancake mix (Bisquick).
Beat until smooth. Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Top with sausage links.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: layered salad
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, green onion and mustard.
Set aside.
In 3-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, macaroni, cucumber, tomato, chicken and peas.
Spread salad dressing over, sealing to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Sprinkle with bacon and toss.

title: butterless, eggless, milkless fruit cake
directions: Put first 8 ingredients together in saucepan and boil 3 minutes.
Let cool, then add candied fruits, chopped nutmeats, flour, baking powder and soda, dissolved in a little hot water and molasses.
Put in a well-greased and floured cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven between 30 and 45 minutes.

title: crab stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Saute onion, celery in a little margarine, till celery is clear. Add spices. In a bowl mix all ingredients well. Place in caps and sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Bake at 350 for 10-15 minutes.

title: baked oysters
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Add liquid, cracker crumbs, oysters and pepper; mix well.
Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Add to mixture.
Return to baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine rice, water and soup mix and pour in baking dish.
Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt and place on top of rice.
Dot with margarine.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: heart smart roasted potatoes
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes for about 15 minutes or until you can pierce them with a fork without resistance.
Drain them and cut into chunks, still with peel intact.
Sprinkle with Butter Buds and spray with Pam; sprinkle with white pepper and paprika.
Preheat the oven to 375° and spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Bake the potatoes for 15 minutes or until they're nice and crisp and browned.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut up in chunks.
Cover with water and cook until potatoes are soft.
Add butter, milk, salt and pepper to season.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix sour cream, pudding and milk until thick.
Layer with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate immediately.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth. Chill.
Stir before serving.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown.
Add seasoning and soup.
Simmer 15 minutes, covered.
Add cheese, stir until melted. Add rice and let cool.
Cook peppers in boiling water 3 minutes. Cool in ice water.
Stuff and freeze.
If peppers are large, split in half.

title: scratch hotcakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add buttermilk and melted butter.
Stir.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to milk mixture.
Mix only until dry ingredients are blended.
Bake on a hot greased griddle.
Makes 12 to 14 hotcakes.
Very good!
Keeps in refrigerator.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, soup, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Spoon into greased casserole and cover with corn flake crumbs.
Spoon remaining 1/4 cup butter over top. Bake at 300° to 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until ingredients are hot and bubbly throughout.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt butter in shallow pan in oven on low heat.
Stir in salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereal and nuts.
Stir until all pieces are coated.
Heat in oven 45 minutes at 250°.

title: shrimp thermidor in casserole
directions: Melt butter; add flour and blend until smooth.
Add warm milk slowly, stirring continuously.
Cook until thick, then simmer about 5 minutes, stirring.

Add wine and all other ingredients. Cook together several minutes, stirring gently but continuously. If too thick, add a little more cream or milk, but it should be quite thick as it will soften during cooking.
Pour into a large casserole; spread smoothly and sprinkle with paprika if you like. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes if ingredients are warm, or for 40 minutes if casserole has been refrigerated.
If top is not brown when time is up, place it under broiler a few minutes, watching closely.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut in large pieces.
Saute sliced mushrooms and onion.
Combine undiluted soups and add milk.
Layer chicken, mushroom and onions and top with soup mixture.
Prepare stuffing according to directions and put over chicken mixture. Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: herbed salmon steaks
directions: Place frozen fish in greased casserole.
Mix lemon juice, marjoram leaves and onion salt.
Spoon on fish and bake at 450° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: salmon or tuna loaf
directions: Mince fish (remove bones). Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Put in greased 8 or 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onions and crawfish.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve over hot rice or fettucine noodles.

title: creamed spiced green beans
directions: Combine
beans,
cheese,
milk and onion salt in baking dish. Crumble
shredded wheat mix with melted butter.
Sprinkle over green beans.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Add 1/2 cup margarine and stir in grits. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is the consistency of oatmeal.
Remove from heat; add salt and pepper.
Beat mixture with egg beater.
Add grated cheese and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This can be made the day before and baked the morning of the brunch.

title: clam chowder
directions: Melt butter and saute onions. Add soups, clams and half and half alternately. Cook on low 3 1/2 hours on top of stove or on low 6 1/2 hours in crock-pot.

title: crustellis (crullers)
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt well.
Add whiskey and eggs; knead for a while, adding more flour if necessary.
The dough should be like noodle dough.

title: chocolate sheet cake(texas sheet cake)
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil the butter/margarine, cocoa and water.
Pour the cocoa mixture over the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add the eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Blend together until mixed.
Bake in 350° oven in a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan (greased and floured) for 20 minutes.
While cake is baking, make icing.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream
cheese,
ounces Cool Whip (save other 1/2 for topping),
peanut
butter
and powdered sugar.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with other 1/2 Cool Whip.
Top with nuts, if desired.

title: herb baked scallops
directions: Wash scallops in cold water; drain thoroughly between sheets of paper toweling.
Place in a single layer in a large shallow baking dish; dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Bake in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Stir scallops to coat well with butter mixture.
Bake 20 minutes longer or until tender.
Serve buttery sauce from dish over mashed or baked potatoes, if you wish.

title: isabelle's famous coffee cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and pudding.
Make hole in center.
Put in oil, sour cream and eggs.
Mix well.
In small bowl, mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Put layer of batter, layer of sugar, cinnamon and nuts in a greased, floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat layer of each.
Swirl with knife.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mash squash.
Saute bell pepper, onion and celery in butter until tender, then add soups.
Bake Korn Kit cornbread and crumble into mixture.
Last, beat 4 eggs until light.
Add to mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain.
Cook rice according to box directions.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix all together; spread mixture on flour tortillas, roll up and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Mix well all ingredients together and use as a spread or dip. (Sociables crackers are good with this.)

title: chocolate nut sundae chiffon
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl. Make a well.
Add oil, egg yolks, water and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
In a large mixer bowl, put 1/2 cup egg whites (4) and cream of tartar.
Beat to very stiff peaks, stiffer than meringue.
Do not underbeat.
Pour yolk mixture slowly over whites, gently folding with rubber scraper until smoothly blended.
Don't stir or beat.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until top springs back when lightly touched.
Turn pan upside down, resting edges on two other pans to cool.
When cool, loosen edges with spatula.
Turn pan over and hit edge sharply to loosen cake.
Ice with 2-Tone Icing.

title: grapefruit salad
directions: Combine gelatin and sugar in boiling water; add cream cheese. Stir to mix. Fold in grapefruit sections and pecans and store in refrigerator until set. Serves 12 to 15.

title: foolproof and fabulous purim hamentashen
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, egg and milk.
Mix.
Stir in rest and blend.
Refrigerate dough 1 hour.
Roll out onto floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 3-inch circles.
Place teaspoon of desired preserves in center of each round.
Fold three sides over, pinching edges together to form a triangle.
Bake on lightly greased baking sheet in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: the earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread coconut in bottom of pan.
Prepare German chocolate cake mix as package directs. Pour batter over coconut and pecans.

title: souper oniony meat loaf for 2
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: herbed buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In medium size bowl stir in flour, baking powder and baking soda to mix well; using pastry blender or two knives, cut in margarine until coarse crumbs form.
Stir buttermilk and chopped herbs into flour mixture only until just blended.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface; knead four or five times until mixture holds together.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness, using 2-inch round cutter, cut out biscuits.
Re-roll and cut out scraps.
Place biscuits on ungreased large cookie sheet, bake 12 to 15 minutes until golden.
Serve warm.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Heat white corn syrup and sugar on medium-high until it boils, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add crunchy peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Mix.
Have pan buttered and pour in. Mash down with buttered hands.

title: fresh apple slaw
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well. Combine cabbage and apples; pour sour cream mixture over top. Stir well. Chill at least 1 hour before serving. Yields 8 servings.

title: brown and serve rolls
directions: Microwave milk 1 1/2 minutes. Then add sugar, salt and oleo. Let cool to at least 110°. In separate bowl, yeast, water and sugar. Combine both mixtures in large bowl. Add 2 1/4 cups flour; mix. Then work in another 2 1/4 cups flour. Cover the top with oil and cover with cloth. Let rise 1 1/2 hours (or until double). Make into rolls (cloverleaf or double) and place in muffin tins. Set aside and let rise until double in size. Bake at 275° for 20 to 30 minutes; DO NOT BROWN. Cool in pan. Place cooled rolls in Ziploc bags; can refrigerate for 5 days or freeze for later. When ready to use, just brown at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: chunky cider applesauce
directions: Combine apples, cider
and lemon juice in 3-quart saucepan. Bring to boil over medium heat and simmer until apples are tender,
about 20 minutes.
Add sugar, salt and nutmeg; cook 1 minute longer.
Break
up apples into chunks.
Cool and refrigerate until serving time.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop by teaspoonfuls into oil. Fry until golden brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk, eggs and salt in large saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly with a whisk or slotted spoon until bubbling.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla, stirring until the butter melts.
Add coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Cool. Top with whipped cream and toasted coconut.
Chill.

title: pork chop dinner bake
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet and brown chips on both sides. Butter a large baking dish which has a well fitting cover. Arrange potatoes and onions in layers. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Mix Worcestershire sauce, mushroom soup and milk and pour over top. Cover tightly and bake at 375° about 50 minutes or until chops are very tender. Remove lid for the last few minutes for browning. Serves 6.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Drop peaches in hot water just long enough to loosen the skin. Peel peaches and drop in pan of cold salt water to retain their color.
Add sugar, vinegar and red hots to a large pot and bring to a boil.
Add peaches.
Cook until tender.
Put into hot sterile jars and seal with hot lids or process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: sunday pot roast
directions: Cut beef into serving size pieces. Prepare vegetables by cutting into chunks. Place all vegetables in slow cooker. Sprinkle rosemary and thyme over vegetables. Arrange beef over vegetables. Pour broth over beef. Cover slow cooker. Cook on low for 8
1/2 to 9 hours or until beef is fork tender.

title: beef tenderloin with creamy chipolte sauce
directions: Combine garlic and oil.
Salt and pepper the roast and rub with garlic mixture.
Place in a baking pan.
Add a little water to pan.
Roast at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove roast from pan and let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
Prepare Chipolte Sauce.

title: cinnamon syrup
directions: Combine sugar, water, corn syrup and cinnamon in saucepan. Bring to a boil; cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, flavoring(s) and butter.
Serve warm with French toast.

title: beef chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook ground beef, celery, onion and green pepper until meat is browned; drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, soup, corn and thyme.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and apple.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix sugar mixture.
Add pecans.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into greased 10 x 6 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Yield: 1 loaf.

title: asparagus with tomatoes
directions: Steam asparagus to desired doneness.
Heat together the mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add to tomato.
Pour over asparagus.

title: summer salad
directions: In a large bowl shred lettuce, next slice cauliflower and then put mayonnaise on top of cauliflower.
Next slice onion; then fry bacon and crumble over onion.
Then spread Parmesan cheese and sugar on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Right before you are ready to eat, mix the salad together.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large dish.
Add corn, corn muffin mix, sour cream, egg and mix well.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all together and serve over crushed ice.
Serves 35 people.

title: pizza salad
directions: In a screwtop jar combine tomato sauce, oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Cover and shake.
Chill. Combine lettuce, cheeses, tomatoes, green pepper, olives and chives.
Shake dressing.
Pour some over salad.
Toss to coat. Pass remaining dressing.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix together all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add pumpkin, water, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 1 bread.

title: lebanese marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix together first four ingredients, pour over mushrooms and marinate overnight.
Should be placed in broiler for a couple of minutes.

title: easy chicken and noodles
directions: Separate meat from skin, fat and bones.
Put skin and bones in large pan. Cover with water and add bay leaves.
Bring to a boil and simmer 1 hour.
Strain broth.
In large pan, put broth and chicken.
Bring to a boil and add frozen noodles, thyme, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until noodles are done, approximately 40 minutes.

title: oyster casserole
directions: You will need a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: creamy onion dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream and the onion soup mix together.
Combine everything until fluffy.
Chill up to 24 hours.
If dip thickens after chilling, stir in 1 or 2 tablespoons milk.
Serve with vegetables, crackers or chips. Makes 2 cups.

title: squash pie
directions: Cook the squash; measure out 3 cups.
Add sugar, milk, egg yolks and rest of the ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Beat the 4 egg whites with 1/4 cup of sugar. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In saucepan, saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour and salt. Gradually add milk.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Add broth, broccoli and carrots.
Simmer until carrots are tender.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, salt, pepper, chili powder and green pepper, then you add 1/2 bottle of Open Pit sauce, 1/2 bottle of catsup, vinegar and sugar.
Let simmer for 20 minutes. It's yummy!

title: pretzel and strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzels and margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt oleo. Pour in flour and nuts. Spread evenly in 11 x 7-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 375°. Let cool completely.

Mix sugar, cream cheese and half of Cool Whip. Spread evenly over first layer. Mix pudding according to directions on box. Spread evenly over second layer. Spread remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts. Chill.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll and shape into cookies.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: tom's waffles
directions: Sift together dry ingredients twice; add gradually milk and mix
with
well
beaten egg yolks and Wesson oil.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.	Bake on hot waffle iron.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill. Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together sugars, cinnamon and pecans; set aside.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and roll in dry mixture, coating well. Layer coated biscuit pieces in tube pan.
Pour melted margarine over top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Real good served warm with coffee.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a heavy skillet.
Add onion and cook slowly until transparent.
Remove and set aside.
Cut beef in 1 x 2 1/2-inch strips.
Turn head to medium-high and cook briefly, turning to brown on all sides.
Remove beef and set aside with onion.
Add remaining 3 tablespoons butter to skillet.
Stir in mushrooms; cover and cook 3 minutes.
Season with pepper and nutmeg.
Whisk sour cream and add to pan; do not allow it to boil. Return beef and onion to pan and just heat through.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Place 1/2 of the bread cubes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with cream cheese cubes; top with remaining bread cubes. Beat eggs with milk and syrup. Pour over bread mix. Refrigerate overnight. Set oven to 350°. Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. Top with syrup or anything else you wish.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Break 1/2 of cake into bite-size pieces and put in punch bowl. Mix pudding according to directions.
Spread 1/2 of pudding over cake pieces.
Spoon 1/2 of pineapple with juice on top
of pudding.
Spread 1 can of pie filling on top of that.
Spread 1/2 of Cool Whip over pie filling.
Add 1/2 of nuts.
Repeat, using the rest of the ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: In saucepan combine all ingredients except apples.
Bring to a boil until thickened.
Pour over apples and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until apples are tender.

title: dill pickles and such
directions: Bring vinegar and salt to boil.
Pack cucumbers in quart jars (cleaned and prepared for canning) with alum and dill weed.
Pour boiling liquid over cucumbers and seal.
Let stand for 6 weeks before using.
If you like kosher, add garlic and hot peppers. Liquid may be used for green tomatoes, small okra, hot peppers, banana peppers, cauliflower or carrots.

title: rice hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, chopped onions and salt; slightly drain.
Mix all the remaining ingredients with the hamburger.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, then bake 20 more minutes, uncovered, with Chinese noodles on top (you may place noodles on top after cooked).

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with crackers, bread, etc.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, broth, soup and vegetables.
Put in a 2-quart dish.
Melt margarine; mix in flour and milk.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cutlets ala ada
directions: Bread the meat and saute until brown. Add sliced onion and olives. Mix 1/4 cup flour and 1 cup water.
Pour into skillet with the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 35 to 45 minutes.
Buon appetito!

title: noodle pizza casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and pour 1/2 into a casserole dish. Combine cheeses and spread 1/2 on top of ground beef mixture.
Pour the remaining meat mixture on top of cheese.
Spread the rest of the cheeses of top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: mexican frank bake
directions: Cut frankfurters lengthwise, being careful not to cut completely through.
Arrange cut side up in a 12 x 18-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs, corn, pickle relish and onion.
Place corn mixture evenly over frankfurters.
Combine soup, water and oregano.
Spoon over mixture and franks.
Bake in moderately hot oven at 375° until thoroughly heated and lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: party pizzas
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients. Separate each biscuit into 3 pizza rounds. Spread with mixture. Put pizzas on cookie sheet and freeze. Remove from cookie sheet and store in plastic bags. Bake frozen pizzas at 425 degrees for 10 minutes. Makes 90 appetizers.

title: spinach-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook spinach and broccoli as directed; drain well.
Combine sour cream and soup mix.
Stir into spinach and broccoli.
Season with salt.
Place in a casserole.
Bake in a 325 degree oven for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with grated cheese.
Serves 8.

title: sweet-n-sour pork
directions: Cube pork, sprinkle with salt and pepper and set aside.
Cube onion and pepper into chunks.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Sprinkle garlic over pepper and onion.
Beat egg and mix in flour and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Coat pork with this batter and deep fry in oil until brown.
Remove pork and drain.
Discard oil.
Next make sauce by combining the water, ketchup, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce and pineapple juice.
Carefully add in cornstarch, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened over low heat.
Saute onion and pepper until tender crisp, drain any oil, add pineapple, add pork, add sauce, stir and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: different fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruits and reserve juices.
Mix 1/3 cup orange juice and 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Add 1/3 cup reserved pineapple juice and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Stir and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour hot mixture over the fruits in a bowl.
Let set, uncovered, until cool, then refrigerate.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease pan.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Add pineapple, oil, vanilla, eggs and bananas.
Mix together well (do not beat).
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: green plantain fritters (fritos verdes - tostones)
directions: Peel and slice the plantains into 1-inch diagonal pieces.
Mix the water with the salt and soak the slices in the refrigerator for 30 minutes (optional).
Fry on both sides in medium-hot oil until they turn slightly bright yellow color.
Remove the slices from the pan and place in paper towels.
Press slices with Tostonera or small plate or the bottom of a heavy jar.
Fry the pressed slices again until they turn a light golden color and are crispy.
Serve immediately.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake into pieces. Set aside; then mix strawberries and glaze together. Set aside.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water until tender.
Drain and save water.
Mash potatoes and return to water they were cooked in. Add milk, margarine, salt and pepper to mixture and heat.

title: eggs  o'brien
directions: Fry pepperoni; add potatoes and margarine to pan.
Cook 10 minutes, uncovered.
Beat eggs, milk and seasoning.
Pour eggs over potatoes.
Slice or grate cheese and put on top of egg/potato mixture.
Cover and cook at 200° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans at least 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Put soaked beans in kettle with 4 cups of water.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer about 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Heat olive oil in medium skillet.
Add onion, 1/2 garlic, cumin and carrot.
Saute over medium heat until carrot is just tender.
Add rest of garlic and bell pepper.
Saute until everything is tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Add to beans.
Stir in orange juice, black pepper and cayenne.
Puree all or part of soup in food processor or blender.) This step makes thicker soup and is optional.
Simmer on low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
(Better made 12 to 24 hours ahead.) Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: favorite broccoli bake
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and sides of 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef in large chunks; drain.
Place beef, broccoli, 1/2 can onions and tomatoes in potato shell.
Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 or 3 minutes more.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix and heat.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: dump cake
directions: Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in the order given and cover with foil.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Put vegetables and meat in heavy skillet, casserole or Dutch oven with tight lid.
Sprinkle tapioca and salt over vegetables and meat.
Pour V-8 juice over all; cook at 250° for 5 hours.
Do not remove lid until 5 hours are up!

title: stuffed mushrooms(great appetizer when having a nice dinner for two)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash mushrooms and drain on paper towel. Pull stems from mushrooms and finely chop.
Melt butter in a small skillet over medium-low heat.
Add chopped mushroom stems and onion.
Saute until tender and translucent.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, soft breadcrumbs, cheese and salt and pepper.
Salt insides of mushroom caps and fill with sauteed mixture, mounding slightly. Add 2 Tbsp. water to shallow baking dish.
Arrange mushroom caps in dish.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 to 10 appetizers.

title: worcestered roll-ups
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain grease.
Combine with cheeses.
Combine marinara and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover bottom of 8 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 cup of this sauce.
Place about 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture on the end of a lasagna noodles, roll up and place in dish.
Continue with remaining noodles. Spoon remaining sauce over each roll-up.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
(This may also be heated in microwave oven.)

title: quick and hearty soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together, drain
In a large kettle, cook rotini following package directions.
Drain.
Stir tomato soup, bouillon and water in kettle, add beef and canned vegetables.
Simmer for ten minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients; mix well. Place in 4 1/2 x 8-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour; drain.
tags: Del Monte Italian style stewed tomatoes

title: orange jello salad
directions: Put oranges and pineapple in a strainer; drain well.
Add dry jello and stir; then add cottage cheese, stirring well.
Add whipped cream and mix well.
Refrigerate and enjoy.

title: homemade wine
directions: Squeeze and mash fruit until it is broken to release juices. Add sugar and mix.
Put in large, airtight container, glass, crock or plastic bucket with plastic tubing leading to a gallon jug of water.
Allow to ferment in warm place (70° to 90°) for 12 to 20 days, depending on temperature.
Strain well and repeat fermenting process with strained juice.
Add sugar (12 to 15 days).
Pour in wine bottles and cork.

title: church cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups hot water in large saucepan for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; add all other ingredients in same saucepan.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg salad sandwiches
directions: Chop eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on sandwich bread.

title: black cake
directions: Sift
together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.	Add eggs, oil, coffee, sour milk and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed 2 minutes. Pour batter
into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven 40	minutes,
or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan on rack. Frost with Hundred Dollar Frosting.

title: chicken soba
directions: Mix soup, milk, chilies, chicken, onion and water.
Heat thoroughly.
Cut tortillas in 4 pieces.
Line casserole pan with tortillas, layer of soup mixture and cheese.
Continue until all ingredients are used.
End with cheese on top.
Heat at 350° until bubbly.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in thawed strawberries, sugar and salt.
Cool until the mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in "whipped" cream.
Cover bottom of Pyrex with torn cake.
Spoon half of strawberry and cream mixture over cake. Alternate layers.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.
Cut in squares.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Spread the rice mix over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle seasoning mix over it.
Lay chicken over it and add soups.
Mix dry (part) Lipton soup mix with a little water and pour into pan.
Pour in rest of water and sprinkle onion mix over it.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
No peek.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Place Dutch oven on medium heat.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
When pan is hot enough to brown butter, add meat and brown both sides.
Place potatoes around meat, turning them in browned fat.
Pack carrots and onions between potatoes close to meat.
Add peppers.
Cover.
Use medium heat for 3 minutes or until steam begins to escape.
Reduce heat to low and cook for 2 1/2 hours.

title: pheasant in sour cream
directions: Fry the pheasants like chicken.
Put in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over the pheasants.
Bake a 325° for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add milk to beaten egg. Pour into dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
Stir in molasses and fat.
Pour batter into greased, shallow pan (about 8-inch square).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: thrifty pound cake
directions: Sift
together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Put into a large mixing bowl the shortening or butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon extract or rind.
Beat at #8 speed for 2
1/2 minutes.
Turn to #3 speed (slow) and add flour mixture alternately
with
buttermilk;
beat only long enough to blend well,
about
minutes.
Pour
into
tube
or
loaf pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cheese beef casserole
directions: Brown meat, green pepper, onion and garlic.
Drain fat.
Add cooked macaroni and tomato soup.
In casserole dish, alternate meat mixture with slices of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: salmon and goat cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend first 5 ingredients in a small bowl.
Arrange bread on baking sheet and brush lightly with oil. Bake until crisp, about 10 minutes.
Cool.
(Can be made up to 6 hours ahead.
Cover mustard mixture and bread separately; let stand at room temperature.)
Spread bread slices with goat cheese, then mustard mixture.
Top with salmon and garnish with dill if desired.

title: sand tarts
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Work in flour, about a cup at a time to make very stiff dough.
Pat into ball; wrap with aluminum foil or plastic wrap and chill overnight. Roll dough, about 1/4 at a time, as thin as possible.
Cut into rounds with cookie cutter or fancy shapes.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Brush tops with egg yolk glaze.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato bake
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until just soft.
Cool.
Grate.
Mix remaining ingredients with potatoes.
Bake in greased casserole 30 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Combine.
Heat over medium heat. Stir frequently until thick.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Mix ingredients. Don't worry if ginger floats on top; just mix as well as possible.
Pour over chicken pieces (with or without skin and cut in strips or not).
Marinate 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning chicken pieces over halfway through baking time.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients, adding nuts and carrots last.
Bake in Bundt pan for about 1 hour at 375°.

title: leslie's spaghetti pie
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions and drain.
In a large bowl mix butter, Parmesan, salt, pepper and egg.
Add spaghetti and toss to coat well.
Spread evenly in 13 x 9-inch pan. Brown ground chuck in large saucepan.
Add onion, pepper and garlic just as meat starts to cook.
Drain off fat when meat is browned. Stir in spaghetti sauce, sugar and oregano.
Spread Ricotta over spaghetti layer; top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella; bake another 10 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: crock-pot pork roast
directions: Slice onion and place in bottom of crock-pot.
Place roast on top of onion.
Salt and pepper roast. Pour the soup over the roast.
Cook 8 hours on low setting or until roast is tender.

title: dr. lisa's grandma's refrigerator pickles
directions: Put a layer of cucumber, alternating with a layer of onion until a gallon jar is packed full.
Mix vinegar, salt, sugar and spices.
Pour over cucumbers and put in refrigerator.
They are ready to eat in 5 days and will keep up to 9 months.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Shred cabbage and slice onions.
Brown almonds and sesame seed in small amount of butter. Mix all together.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Heat Jell-O and pineapple until it boils and dissolves.
Add 1 1/2 cups buttermilk and
9 ounces Cool Whip.
Mix.
Chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, pineapple, onion, salt and green pepper; mix well.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Fry sausage and cut into bite size pieces.
Arrange bread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; cover with cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and mustard; add mushrooms.
Pour over top, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Dilute soup with milk; pour over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Prepare marinade first in a large bowl, stirring frequently. Cook carrots in salted boiling water until tender-crisp, 5 or 6 minutes.
Drain and while carrots are still hot, stir them into marinade mixture.
Refrigerate 24 to 48 hours.
Toss several times. Serve cold.
Serves 8.

title: chicken with sour cream
directions: Mix the soup, sour cream, sherry and mushrooms (don't use juice) together.
Layer chicken in pan.
Pour sauce over chicken; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine ingredients.
Simmer for about 4 minutes; place in jars.
Keep for several days in refrigerator to allow juice to permeate before serving as hors d'oeuvre.

title: mexican creole cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Sift together the flour, cocoa and salt.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Mix baking soda with boiling water and add to mixture (makes a very thin batter).
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: dry lima bean crock-pot recipe
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir together well.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 10 hours or on High 4 to 5 hours.
Goes great with cornbread.

title: oven parmesan potato chips
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on a greased baking sheet in a single layer.
Mix butter, onion, salt, pepper and paprika.
Brush on one side of potatoes, then turn and brush other side.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: presidential cinnamon-glazed almonds
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place butter on a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan and place in oven to melt, about 7 minutes. Meanwhile, beat egg whites with salt until frothy; gradually add sugar and beat to stiff peaks.
Gently fold in almonds and cinnamon.
Pour mixture onto jelly roll pan, toss with butter. Bake about 40 minutes, tossing every 10 minutes, until almonds are crisp.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Spoon into a greased 8-inch ovenproof dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Cook noodles in salted water until done.
Rinse and drain well.
Grate cabbage, salt, let stand for a few moments and squeeze out well.
Brown cabbage in oil.
Pour melted butter over noodles, and add cabbage and serve hot.

title: warm orange - spiced fruit
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until fruit is tender and mixture is thickened, stirring occasionally.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, drained pineapple, green pepper, onion and 1 cup of nuts.
Mix well.
Form a ball and roll in other cup of nuts.

title: chewy butterscotch bars
directions: Put butter or margarine and brown sugar in saucepan on low heat.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time; stir.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, combined with baking powder.
Stir well.
Add nuts.
Stir.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cool shrimp pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Unroll dough and pat dough evenly onto 12-inch greased pizza pan, sealing perforations. Bake for 11 to 13 minutes or until crust is light golden brown. Remove pan from oven. Cool completely on a wire rack.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Split chicken in halves.
Brown in shortening (do not use flour).
Place chicken in roasting pan.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until tender.

title: cauliflower and pea salad
directions: Break cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Run cold water over peas in a colander to thaw.
Drain well.
Mix Hidden Valley with mayonnaise.
Toss dressing with vegetables and marinate.
Chill.

title: clarice's broiled chicken
directions: Put chicken in bowl.
Pour vinegar over it.
Crush garlic with salt and pepper and rub over all chicken pieces.
Let marinate in covered bowl with onion slices mixed in.
Preheat broiler.
Place onion slices in bottom of broiler pan.
Put chicken pieces on top and dot with butter.
Broil until done.
Mix evaporated milk and sugar with juices in the bowl and pour over chicken in pan.
Broil for a few additional minutes.
Serve with rice, green peas and shredded carrot salad.

title: cheese dip
directions: Add all ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot leaving top off.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: In large bowl, combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, the sour cream, pepper, pimiento and 1/2 can of onion rings.
Pour into shallow 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions in diagonal rows across top; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk, eggs, vanilla and then baking powder.
Add 1 cup of flour at a time.
Chill for 2 hours. Roll out thin and cut into fun shapes.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Salt and pepper each chicken breast.
Lay in greased casserole pan.

title: patio potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil peeled 1-inch pieces of carrots for 10 to 20 minutes until soft, not soggy.
Put oil, sugar, vinegar, pepper, salt and soup in blender; mix for 5 minutes.
Pour over drained carrots and onion rings; let stand overnight (in refrigerator).
Carrots should marinate at least 12 hours.
Serve cold, as an appetizer.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: ground beef grand style
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add softened cream cheese and other ingredients.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze some water from spinach.
Blend with mayo and sour cream.
Stir in chopped onions and vegetable soup.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve in a scooped out pumpernickel bread, saving the cut-out cubed bread for dipping along with vegetables.

title: easy chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix melted margarine with dressing mix.
Mix soup and chicken broth.
Place dressing mix in bottom of long baking dish.
Cut up cooked chicken pieces and place on top.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Sprinkle top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 300°.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Saute onion and garlic (not brown).
Add cheese.
Stir.
Add soup, mushrooms and flour to broccoli and mix well.
Add croutons on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Enjoy.

title: spinach and egg salad with yogurt
directions: Wash the spinach thoroughly.
Drain.
Dry with paper towels. Shred and combine with the scallions in salad bowl.
Beat the yogurt, olive oil and salt and pepper with a fork until well blended.
Add the eggs.
Pour the mixture over the spinach.
Mix gently, but thoroughly, taking care not to mash the eggs.
Taste for seasoning. Garnish with olives.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix and chill.
Form into a ball.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: dieters striped delight
directions: Mix butter and Sweet 'N Low in crumbs.
Make into crust in pan.
Put a layer of pudding on graham cracker crust.
Then put a layer of cream cheese, then layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle some graham cracker crumbs on top.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Blend ingredients and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until done.

title: country style steak
directions: Lightly brown steak in oil.
Salt and pepper (careful not to use too much salt).
Place in baking dish after browning.
Pour off excess oil from frying pan.
Put soup in this pan and add water.
Stir well to mix and remove drippings from bottom of pan. Pour this over steak and bake in 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until tender.

title: fruit punch
directions: Place pears, lemonade and water in blender and blend until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: cheesy baked grits recipe
directions: Pour water over instant grits and cheese, stirring well to blend.
Add small amount of hot grits to egg.
Add egg mixture and milk to grits, stirring quickly.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated moderate oven at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes. Serve hot with butter.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Make graham cracker base as directed on package.
