Let stand 1 to 2 hours.
Mix softened cream cheese with Dream Whip (prepared as directed on package).
Spread over graham cracker base.
Let stand 1 hour.
Then spread cherry pie filling over the cream cheese and Dream Whip topping.

title: mama's tea cakes
directions: Use flour enough to make a soft dough.
Roll thin and cut into desired shapes.
Dough will roll better if it sits awhile.
Bake on well-greased cookie sheet at 325° to 350° for 6 to 10 minutes.

title: won ton filler(or egg roll)
directions: Cook pork, drain excess oil; add green onions and balance of ingredients.
Mix all with 2 tablespoons peanut butter.
Use 2 large packages of won ton skins.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onion in small amount of margarine.
Add green chilies, 1/2 can mushroom soup, 1 cup sour cream and shredded chicken and heat together.
Place a spoonfull of chicken mixture into tortillas.
Add shredded cheese.
Roll.
Place seam side down in casserole dish.
Add 1/2 can soup and remaining sour cream mixed together.
Pour over tortillas.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Shape into small balls.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Use fancy toothpicks for serving.
Makes 30 or so small sausage balls.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 9 inch x 13 inch pan.
Cool completely.
Crumble.
Mix together pudding, milk and spices.
Add pumpkin.
In large bowl, layer crumbled cake, pumpkin and Cool Whip.
End with crumbled cake on top.

title: meal in a bowl pasta salad
directions: Cook your pasta and let it drain well.
Prepare all vegetables.
Mix the seasoning.
Combine all ingredients and toss. Store salad in the refrigerator at least an hour before serving to let the seasoning do its magic.

title: mexi-dip
directions: Spread beans on flat dish or pan (baking sheet).
Spread the sour cream on beans.
Sprinkle chopped tomatoes, then green onions.
Next, add picante sauce.
Top with a few olives and slices of avocado.

title: caribbean banana fritters
directions: Crush bananas; add sugar, cinnamon, raisins and vanilla.
Mix; add eggs and flour (if large bananas, use 2 small or 1 extra large egg).
Fry in oil and then top with warm rum.

title: jello-cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle the dry orange jello into the cottage cheese.
Put in the refrigerator for a few hours.
Drain the fruit; add to the cottage cheese-jello mixture.
Return to the refrigerator.
One hour before serving, mix in the Cool Whip.

title: our favorite meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Pat mixture in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: apricot pork chops
directions: Mix preserves, lemon juice and mustard together.
Grease a baking dish.
Sprinkle pork chops on both sides with salt.
Then arrange in a baking dish.
Spoon ingredients over chops, turning them to coat.
Place in a 425° oven and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until pork chops are cooked through.
Serve with pan juices.

title: lime delight
directions: In a saucepan, bring pineapple to boil over medium heat. Remove from heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened, about 30 minutes.
Stir in cottage cheese and whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in glass or metal pan.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Pour over peaches.
Sift flour and salt; blend in Crisco. Add milk.
Spoon flour mixture over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: atholl brose(scottish dish)
directions: Toast oatmeal by tossing and stirring over medium heat in nonstick pan.
Let cool.
Mix honey and whiskey together.
Whip cream until it forms soft peaks, then fold in honey-whiskey mixture.
Chill.
Just before serving, stir in oatmeal.
Put raspberries, blueberries or mixture into tall glass or bowls then spoon Atholl Brose over.
Enjoy.
Serves 4.

title: baked chicken breast supreme
directions: Mix together the sour cream, lemon juice, celery salt, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and garlic.
Coat chicken with this mixture.
Marinate overnight.

title: corn bread salad(makes 12 servings)
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Set aside.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and bell pepper. Drain well. Add salt, pepper, soups, corn and sauce.
Mix well. Simmer 10 minutes.
In a large casserole dish, layer meat mixture, chips and cheese, ending with cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: drop rolls
directions: Mix sugar and melted butter.
Add egg and dry yeast, dissolved in warm water.
Add flour.
Drop by spoonfuls in muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
This mixture will keep for one week in the refrigerator.
Put mixture in an airtight container.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Grind wafers into powder.
Mix milk into batter.
Melt marshmallows in about 2 tablespoons of water.
Mix together good. Will be thick and sticky.
Put in a loaf pan.
Place in refrigerator for about 2 days until firm.

title: turkey and stuffing meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Shape into two meat loaves on baking rack.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.
Serve with seasoned sweet potatoes.
tags: Stove Top stuffing and seasoning mix

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash avocados and add remaining ingredients.
Blend.
Add more or less seasoning, as you desire.

title: crab salad
directions: Chop all ingredients and mix well.

title: mammy's peach pie
directions: Melt butter in oblong 13 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together sugar, flour, milk and peach juice.,
Pour over melted butter.
Do not mix!
Pour peaches over mixture.
Do not mix!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Add all ingredients together and mix in food processor or with mixer.

title: pea pods-almonds-mushrooms
directions: Mix together water, soy sauce, cornstarch and bouillon.
Now, melt 2 tablespoons butter in a skillet; add slivered almonds. Stir-fry until lightly browned; add pea pods.
Stir-fry 2 minutes more.
Now add mushrooms after they have been drained.
Add cornstarch mixture; cook and stir until thickened.
Serve.

title: cornbread fritters(usa)
directions: Make a thick batter with meal and milk.
Drop by spoonfuls on a well-greased hot skillet or griddle.
Fry until golden brown on each side.
Serve hot with butter.
Yields 10 to 12.

title: guacamole dip casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed in a 9 x 13 inch casserole.
Serve with chips.

title: crab casserole i
directions: Saute artichoke hearts and mushrooms separately.
Mix well with remaining ingredients, except cheese.	Put in 3 quart casserole.	Sprinkle cheese over mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until heated through.
Serve 12.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into serving size pieces.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour and salt. Dredge steak in flour mixture. Brown in hot oil in a large skillet.
Remove from skillet and place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Set aside.
Add 2 tablespoons flour to pan drippings.
Cook over medium heat 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add tomatoes, celery, carrots and onion.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Stir in soy sauce.
Pour mixture over steak. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until steak is tender.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Cook sausage and then drain and wash with hot water.
Return to skillet but get hot and add 8 oz. cream cheese.
Stir well. Roll out package of crescent rolls on cabinet.
Put sausage mixture on rolls.
Roll up.
Butter good and cook until brown. Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: quick marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix red wine, salt, sugar, pepper and garlic together with a whisk.
Slowly add oil.
Mix so that mixture doesn't separate, then add onions and mushrooms.
Let marinate 24 hours before serving.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: chocolate dream
directions: Find the most scrumptious looking strawberries.
(Hand picked and large are the best.)
Melt white or milk chocolate morsels in the microwave until soft and gooey.
May need to stir.
Dip strawberries in by holding the stems in the chocolate.
Set aside to cool.
The better quality the chocolate, the better the results.
Enjoy!!

title: fudge cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry). Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: spicy sweet popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn, mix dry ingredients in a Ziploc bag.
Add popcorn and spray with cooking spray.
Close bag and mix.
Repeat with cooking spray until popcorn is coated.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Combine salad oil, sugar, vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add flour, salt and soda to mixture; mix well.
Add apples and nuts. Bake at 350° in a greased Bundt pan.
May add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, if you like.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli heads from stems.
Wash broccoli and put in container.
Combine vinegar, Miracle Whip and sugar together. Pour in container (over broccoli), seal and refrigerate overnight. Fry bacon and crumble.
Before serving, add bacon and sunflower seeds.

title: grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Prepare a medium size skillet with Pam cooking spray or butter. Heat skillet.
Lightly butter one side of each piece of bread.
Lay butter side down; place cheese on top, then place other slice of bread with butter facing up.
Cook on both sides until lightly browned.
Cut into strips or use your favorite cookie cutter for little fingers.

title: mexican wedding cakes (cookies)
directions: Cream butter well; add sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll in balls (1 inch).
If too soft, chill about 15 minutes.
Bake for 10 minutes in 375° oven.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Pour into unbaked graham cracker pie crust.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes until set.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add dates, orange slices (chopped finely) and nuts.
Coat fruit well.
Add flour mixture and coconut to creamed mixture.
This makes a very stiff dough.
Put in greased floured 13 x 9-inch or Bundt pan.
Bake at 250° for about 2 1/2 hours.
Combine orange juice and powdered sugar.
Pour over hot cake.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water; drain.
In a large skillet, saute onion in 5 tablespoons butter; add soup and mix. Add cheese; heat and stir until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in cabbage, salt and pepper.
Transfer to 2-quart baking dish.
Melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter in skillet; stir in bread crumbs until lightly browned.
Sprinkle over cabbage mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out and mash thoroughly.
Add all other ingredients.
Re-fill the shells and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red fruit jelly
directions: Wash the berries.
Place in layers in an enamel saucepan, adding just enough water to cover.
Bring slowly to the boil and simmer until the fruit has all broken up and the juice is dark red in color.
Sieve the juice through a clean, scalded piece of linen or cheesecloth, pressing as much juice out of the berries as possible.
Measure the juice, boil up and thicken with the required amount of corn flour dissolved in a little cold water.
Pour into a bowl, sprinkle with sugar to prevent a skin forming and serve cold with milk or cream.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
While cake is hot, punch holes in the top with a wooden spoon handle.
Mix pineapple with sugar and heat.
Pour pineapple mixture over top of cake.
Prepare pudding as directed and pour over pineapple layer.
Sprinkle layer of chopped nuts over pudding.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: rhubarb coffeecake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add rest of ingredients except rhubarb.
Mix and then fold in diced rhubarb.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Good with a light glaze.

title: zucchini provencal
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, green pepper, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir and let simmer until zucchini is cooked, firm and not mushy.
Place in serving dish and garnish with parsley and Parmesan cheese.

title: texas crawdad's
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tortillas and picant sauce.
Spread the mixture over tortillas.
Roll and refrigerate. Cover overnight.
Cut into slices and serve with picant sauce.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Flour meat, salt and pepper and brown in butter.
Add remaining ingredients, except milk and lemon juice.
Cook over slow heat in cover skillet for 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Stir in milk and lemon juice.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in large casserole dish at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with 1 1/2 cups crushed cornflakes, which has been blended with 2 tablespoons butter. Brown for another 5 or 10 minutes.

title: george's favorite sausage and lentil soup
directions: Heat olive oil in a heavy 6 to 8-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add sausage and cook until almost all fat is rendered. Transfer sausage to a platter.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger with seasoning; drain.
Pour on Doritos chips. Add tomato and cheese.
Pour dressing on top (to taste).
Stir together.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Beat pudding and milk at low speed until thickened.
Add 8 ounces of the Cool Whip; blend in.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer with graham crackers; spread 1/3 of the pudding mixture over crackers.
Repeat twice.
Top with 4 ounce layer of Cool Whip. Sprinkle with a few graham cracker crumbs.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Chill well.

title: baked beans
directions: You will need large mixing bowl and baking pan, 12 x 9 x 2.

title: german potato and franks
directions: Heat oil; brown onions.
Add sliced franks and vinegar, capers, salt and pepper and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain sauerkraut; rinse.
Add to franks; simmer 10 minutes.
Add boiled, sliced potatoes; simmer 10 minutes and then enjoy.

title: french salad dressing(home made)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bottle or jar.
Cover and shake real well.
Refrigerate.

title: impossible pie or quick quicheroswell, new mexico
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion evenly over bottom of plate.
(You can use browned and crumbled sausage instead of bacon.)

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix, chill and serve with crackers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In bowl, beat eggs until foamy; gradually beat in oil and sugar.
Add grated zucchini, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder, mixing well.
Gradually blend in flour, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in chopped walnuts.
Pour into greased Bundt pan (3-quart) and bake at 350° for one hour, or until cake tests done and starts to leave sides of pan.
Cool in pan for ten minutes.
Loosen edge.
Shake loose and turn cake out on rack to cool.
Store in covered tin or wrapped in foil.

title: sugar-free banana walnut cake
directions: Beat together mashed bananas and butter until creamy.
Add eggs and water.
Beat well.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth.
Add nuts.
Spoon butter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cowboy salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in large bowl.
Add dressing and toss. Serves 6 people.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Add flour, baking soda, cocoa, spices and salt.
Add the zucchini.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with nuts and chocolate chips.

title: mrs. "d" poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together in electric mixer for about 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: cucumbers and onions in sour cream
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Add cucumbers and onions; toss gently.
Chill for 24 hours and serve.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: In a 3-quart oblong baking dish, arrange chicken.
Bake 30 minutes.
Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake an additional 30 minutes or until done.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine hamburger and bread crumbs.
Make small meatballs and brown these enough to hold their shape.
Combine remaining ingredients
and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mama's fried pies
directions: Cook apricots and peaches with water.
When tender, add sugar to taste.
Drain; save juice to store remainder of fruit if not all is cooked.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Butter and flour bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread pecans on bottom and coconut on top of pecans.
Mix cake mix in bowl as directed and pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix butter, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Pour over batter and swirl. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until done.
Leave in pan, then pig out!!!

title: sherry good's frito pie
directions: Crumble Fritos and place in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Add a layer of Cheddar cheese, onions and chili; another layer of cheese and top with Fritos.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt candy bars.
Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Add chocolate syrup, candy bars and vanilla.
Pour into tube pan or large cake pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix salad dressing and cream cheese until smooth.
Cut marshmallows into pineapple.
Cut cherries and nutmeats.
Combine and add whipped cream.
Freeze.
Serves 8.

title: fried chicken
directions: Soak skinned chicken in buttermilk for 1 1/2 hours.
Combine flour, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mix; let set for 20 minutes, then fry in oil until nicely browned. Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt butter and honey together; add pecans.
Heat until golden brown.
Pour over chicken and serve with rice.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Grate cheese. Chop pimientos, but do not drain. Mix cheese and pimientos. Add sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar. Stir in mayonnaise. Refrigerate.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Chill and serve.

title: stuffed chicken quarters
directions: Prepare stuffing.
In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt margarine.
Add zucchini and cook until tender, about 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Into saucepan, tear bread into small pieces.
Stir in egg, cheese, pepper and salt.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Loosen skin on each chicken quarter by pushing fingers between skin and meat to form a pocket.
Put in stuffing. Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until fork-tender.
To serve, remove chicken to platter.
Brush with honey and sprinkle with salt.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: Thoroughly mix together, then use 1/4 to 1/2 cup to each pound of hamburger.

title: microwave broccoli soup
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine white sauce.
Mix broth, broccoli, carrot and onion.
Cover with lid or waxed paper. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender, stirring 4 times until soup boils and thickens.
Stir in milk and pepper. Microwave, covered, 2 minutes until hot.

title: brown-edged cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and eggs; beat until light. Add salt and flour.
Mix well.
Drop by half-teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: "party" bread spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise in small bowl. Spread onto slices of any deli or party bread.
Garnish with pieces of your choice of listed garnishes or make up your own.

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and mushroom pieces.
Place half amount of the ingredients in order listed in buttered casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zesty pumpkin soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Saute onion and garlic until soft.
Add curry powder, salt, coriander, red pepper and mushrooms, if desired.
Cook 1 minute.
Add broth and boil gently for 15 to 20 minutes or until mushrooms are soft.
Stir in pumpkin and half and half.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour into blender or food processor and blend until creamy.
Decorate warm, topping with sour cream and chives.
May be kept covered and chilled overnight, bringing to room temperature before reheating.

title: oven baked sesame chicken(great appetizer for parties)
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Cut up chicken breast into small pieces (slightly bigger than bite size).
Mix beaten egg with milk; set aside.
Mix together flour, sesame seed, paprika, pepper, baking powder and salt.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients except for chili powder with hands.
Shape into 2 to 3 logs.
Roll in chili powder.
Now refrigerate.

title: spinach lasagne rolls
directions: Combine above; put on center of lasagne noodles.
Roll up. Cover with favorite spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Wash and cut up chicken and remove skin.
Soak in buttermilk for about 15 minutes.
Take the chicken out of buttermilk.
Season with salt, lemon pepper and garlic powder.
Roll in mixed bread crumbs and flour.
Bake in a pan in the oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: biscuits cream of tartar
directions: Sift flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt into a bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk.
Mix until flour disappears and dough is just right for rolling.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured board. Handle very little.
Shape and flatten to about 1-inch thickness. Cut biscuits and place on a greased sheet.
Add a dot of butter to each biscuit.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add strawberries and stir until thawed. Add bananas and nuts. Pour 1/2 mixture in pan and hold in the refrigerator until firm. Mix sour cream and marshmallows. Spread over firm gelatin. Take the other half and place on top of sour cream and marshmallow mixture. Set until firm.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Freeze in 5-quart ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with electric mixer.
Put in casserole.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serve hot.

title: cream cheese jello salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let cool in large bowl.
Cream together cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Beat well.
Add to jello mixture and refrigerate.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot beet juice. Mix beets and cream cheese. Stir in beets, cream cheese and pineapple. Put in refrigerator to harden. Serve on lettuce leaves topped with mayonnaise.

title: linda's venison stew
directions: Put 2 tablespoons oil in large Teflon coated electric skillet. Pound venison with a meat hammer.
Flour venison; put in hot oil. Fry for about 20 minutes.
Put in salt, pepper and garlic salt. Add a quart of water.
Add the beef bouillon cubes.
While this is cooking, peel and cut up carrots, potatoes, onion and celery and put in a pan of water.
Bring to boil; boil for 15 minutes.
Do not drain.
Add to meat mixture.
Stir.
Add 2 tablespoons flour with water to this.
If it makes it too thick, add a little more water.
If too thin, add a little more flour.
Cook for about 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: spicy peach pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, milk and spices in a saucepan. Prepare as directed on package for pie.
Chill about 10 minutes. Fold in peaches and pour into pie shell.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: family goulash
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Add onion and garlic, cook and stir until onion is tender.
Combine 1 cup water, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, salt, paprika, dry mustard and pepper; stir into ground beef mixture.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Blend cornstarch/flour and 2 tablespoons water and add to meat mixture.
Cook and stir for 5minutes or until sauce thickens and begins to boil.
Cook noodles in water, drain and add to meat mixture.
Serves 4.

title: jimmy mcgowan's famous chili
directions: Brown onions in a large skillet, combine all other ingredients (excluding the ground beef) in a large pot.
Add browned onions to the large pot.
Brown the ground beef, add to large mixture. Simmer until thickened.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Combine beans and barbecue sauce in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place bacon over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir in bacon; sprinkle onion over top and bake another 3 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: gotebki(cabbage rolls)
directions: Saute onion and minced garlic.
Add meat and seasonings.
When cooked, add rice.
Boil water.
Remove core from cabbage and place in the boiling water.
Cover and cook until outer leaves are soft. Remove outer leaves.
Repeat until all leaves are soft and removed.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients; stir until smooth.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: paula's hamburger
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Add 1/2 cup water and 1 tablespoon flour; stir.
Add the hot water, chili sauce and mustard.
Serve over buns.

title: butterfinger candy pie
directions: Beat eggs light in large bowl.
Stir in water, sugar, flour and salt until well combined.
Melt butter in small saucepan over low heat.
Stir hot butter into batter.
Stir in 6 chopped candy bars.
Cool completely.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Spray 9 X 13 pan with Pam.
Mix flour, butter, and sugar and pat into pan.
Bake at 325 degrees until golden brown.
Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar, and add 1 tub of Cool Whip.
Whip until well blended.
Spread over cooled crust.
Spread blueberry pie filling over top.
Chill well.

title: molding clay(not to eat)
directions: Toss apples, brown sugar, flour, sage and onion together and put in casserole dish.
Cut sausage in 1/2-inch slices and arrange on top of apples.
Cover loosely and cook in microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes, until apples are tender.
Sprinkle cheese over top and cook on Medium for 5 minutes to melt cheese.

title: plum bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven. Bake in 1 loaf pan or 2 small loaf pans that are greased and floured.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Rinse and pick over the cranberries.
Drain the raspberries' liquid into a measuring cup and add enough water to make 1 cup total.
Transfer the liquid, the cranberries, raspberries, sugar and orange zest into a deep, non-reactive (such as enamel) saucepan.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine all and marinate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: rye waffles
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Mix egg yolks and milk and add to dry mixture.
Fold in egg whites, leaving a few fluffs. Cook according to waffle maker instructions.
Makes 3 (10-inch) waffles.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes.
Cook potatoes until almost soft, then peel. Put the rest of ingredients together and heat until cheese is melted.
Put in layers in casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: In small bowl, combine first 3 ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl, combine eggs, onion, crackers, ground beef, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 of tomato sauce mixture; mix thoroughly.
Place meat mixture in a glass ring mold or 2-quart microproof round casserole dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top of meat. Cook, covered with waxed paper, in microwave oven on High max power 16 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves six.
Time might be little different on your microwave.

title: banana  nut bread
directions: In mixer bowl, cream together sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in mashed bananas and eggs.
Add biscuit mix and nuts; stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cover with foil the last 15 minutes if bread browns too quickly.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: hash brown potatoes casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together sharp cheese, sour cream, salt and onions.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tropical chicken
directions: Brown chicken pieces in butter.
Add nutmeg, basil and orange juice.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Add cut up potatoes.
Cook 1/2 hour longer.
Add peaches and cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix milk, oil and eggs. Beat until smooth.
Add to dry ingredients.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: debbie's salad dressing
directions: Blend ingredients in blender.
While blender is on, unscrew and pour in salad oil.

title: fried cream of wheat
directions: Follow directions on package.
To simmering Cream of Wheat add the salt, sugar, grated lemon rind, nutmeg and vanilla.
In greased flat pan, pour cooked Cream of Wheat to 1 inch level. Allow to harden.
When completely cooled, cut into 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch strips.
Roll in bread crumbs, then fry in deep fat until brown.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Wash and drain cranberries.
Wash and chop apples with peel or peel apples and chop.
Mix cranberries, apples and sugar and place in buttered casserole.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Add 1 cup oatmeal and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Place on top of fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: big thin pancakes
directions: Mix into a smooth batter.
Put a little Crisco into a large frying pan.
Pour batter so that it will produce a thin pancake. Tilt pan so that batter barely covers bottom of pan with a thin layer.
When ready to turn pancake, place a few drops of shortening on upper side.
Turn with a spatula.
When done, sprinkle with sugar.
Roll up and serve.
They may also be sprinkled with cherries and sugar, then rolled.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes; cool.
Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick. Peel and slice apples.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternately layer potatoes, apples and pineapple, ending with potatoes. Sprinkle each layer with some of sugar, allspice, butter and lemon juice.
Cover and bake for 1 hour or until apples are done. Serves 6.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: chili and cheese dip
directions: Cube cheese and combine with chili in crock-pot. Heat until melted and blended. Serve with nacho chips.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Microwave frozen potatoes for 6 to 8 minutes to thaw.
Mix soup, sour cream and cheese, then mix in potatoes.
Melt butter and mix in corn flakes for topping.
Pour potatoes in greased 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken king ranch
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add chicken broth, soups, chili powder, garlic and tomatoes.
Mix well and let come to a boil.
Remove from stove.

title: meat log
directions: On a piece of aluminum foil, lay out bacon, side by side.
Lay round steak on top of bacon.
Mix together the hamburger and onion soup mix; spread on top of steak.
Carefully roll up to form a log.
Wrap in foil and bake at 375° for approximately 3 hours, depending on how done you want the meat.

title: kass's brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in lightly greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and lightly dust with powdered sugar.

title: lemon afternoon delight
directions: In a large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in rind, juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Chill 4 hours.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: In a double boiler, melt stick of butter and add cubed cream cheese.
Stir over low heat until melted.
In a separate pot, saute crawfish, onions, bell pepper and mushrooms until limp.
Add mushroom soup and cooked rice.
Stir in garlic powder and peppers. Add cream cheese mixture.
Put in greased casserole.
Top with Velveeta cheese and onion rings.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick pea and biscuit casserole
directions: In a small skillet, combine soup and peas with liquid; mix and heat well.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Place biscuits on top and bake in a 375° oven until biscuits are done.
This makes a wonderful, quick lunch.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine in saucepan; add sugar, flour, sour cream and cheese. Pour over broccoli; sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter popsicles
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over the above ingredients and mix. Add 1 cup peanut butter and 1 cup milk.
Pour into tiny Dixie cups or ice cube tray.
Freeze and enjoy!

title: cheddar sausage muffins
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, cook sausage until no longer pink; drain. In a bowl, combine soup, cheese and water. Stir in Bisquick mix until blended. Add sausage. Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks. Serve warm.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into 8 patties.
Fry slowly and brown on both sides.

title: egg and sausage breakfast
directions: The night before serving, cook sausage, separate and drain well.
Mix eggs, milk, soup and dry mustard.
Beat together until foamy.
Combine egg mixture and cooked sausage.
Add grated cheese and bread cubes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan; chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bacon stuffed mushrooms
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Wash and dry mushrooms.
Remove stems, chop and reserve for stuffing. Saute diced bacon, onion, green pepper, chopped mushroom stems, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat when cooked through, not browned.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and drain berries.
Crush enough of the berries to make 1/2
cup
crushed
berries.
Slice	remaining berries in half. Set aside.

title: hamburger cobblers
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat oil in large skillet over moderate heat (about 250°).
Add beef, salt, pepper, garlic and onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, until meat is browned.
Place mixture in bottom of a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Arrange cheese slices in a layer on top.
In a small bowl, combine tomato sauce, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce and blend well.
Pour over cheese. Arrange biscuits in rows on top of sauce.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, or until biscuits are baked through and tops are nicely browned. Serves 4 to 5.

title: shrimp south louisiana
directions: Wash and peel shrimp.
Make roux by heating shortening in a deep skillet.
Add flour and cook on medium heat until dark brown, stirring constantly.
Add chopped vegetables, Ro-Tel tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Season with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Let simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Through cooking times, stir occasionally.
Bring to boiling point; add shrimp.
Cook 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil and debone (or use boneless) chicken breasts; dice.
Dice pepper; saute in 1/2 stick butter.
Add flour and milk to thicken. Add 1/2 of cheese, soup, soy sauce, garlic salt, pimento and mushrooms; mix together well.
Stir in chicken pieces.
Boil spaghetti; drain well and add to mixture.
Mix all ingredients. Pour into casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: club soda waffles
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients in a large bowl. Add Club soda, stirring until batter is blended. Use immediately or will go flat. Ladle onto a preheated waffle iron. The batter doesn't store well so make only as much as you will use at one time or make extra waffles and freeze for later use.

title: *swedish nuts
directions: Toast nuts in slow oven at 325° until light brown.

Fold sugar, salt and vanilla in egg whites (stiff) and add the nuts. Meanwhile, melt butter or oleo in same pan in which nuts were in. Blend nuts well into egg white mixture and put into pan with butter.
Bake in a slow 325° oven for about 30 minutes, until nuts are coated with brown covering and sugar and butter are gone. Spread on waxed paper and separate to cool.
Put in tins and nuts will keep for several months.
Makes about 4 cups of nuts.

title: lemon fruit freeze
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: warm fruit compote
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, combine mixed fruit, nectar, lemon juice and honey.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve hot or chilled.
Serves 8.

title: congo bars
directions: In a bowl, mix dry ingredients together.
Melt shortening; remove from heat.
Add brown sugar; add eggs one at a time; add vanilla; add dry ingredients slowly.
Add chocolate bits.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut and enjoy.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. In large mixer bowl, cream butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch chips.

title: curried spicy potatoes(4 servings)
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender, 30 minutes. Cool.
Peel and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Place in medium bowl.
Add 3 tablespoons of water and curry powder.
Toss to coat.
Season to taste with salt.
Heat vegetable oil in large skillet.
Add shallots and potatoes.
Cook until crusty and golden brown, for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook up broccoli, drain and put in a 2 quart casserole dish. Dump in onions.

title: smokey seafood dip
directions: Blend and chill.
Great for dipping shrimp or veggies!

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together in saltwater. Drain and add cheese, oleo, eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour in buttered casserole and top with cracker crumbs; bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheese straws
directions: Have butter soft and work in flour and grated cheese.
Add Worcestershire and cayenne.
Work into a dough.
Roll out; cut into strips.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: microwave baked custard
directions: Heat milk at High for 3 to 4 minutes to very hot, but not boiling.
Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat until well blended.
Gradually add hot milk, beating well.
Divide mixture evenly between 6 custard cups.
Place cups in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Pour about 1/2 cup hot water around cups.
Cook at Medium (50%) for 8 1/2 minutes, rearranging cups after 3 minutes.
Continue cooking at Medium for 5 minutes, testing for doneness every 30 seconds and removing any that are soft set.

title: barbequed pork on bun
directions: Boil
or
bake
pork
until well done.
When cool, dice into small pieces. Brown onion in fat. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer
30 minutes.
Pour over meat and simmer about 20 minutes. (It is good to make three or four times the amount of sauce
and divide in portions to freeze for later use.)
Serve the hot pork on warm buns.

title: quick casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package and drain.
Saute meat and onions, drain.
Spread noodles in bottom of 3-quart casserole dish.
To meat mixture add other ingredients except cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar.
Slowly add lemon juice and butter. Pour into baked, cooled pastry shell and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato vichyssoise(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add potatoes and stock.
Simmer, partially covered, about 30 minutes.
Puree soup and add cream, sherry and salt.
Chill.

title: mom's date nut candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter until it makes a soft ball in a cup of cold water.
Add dates; continue cooking until it makes a firm ball in a cup of cold water.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and spread on buttered dish.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Melt together margarine and shortening; cream with brown and white sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together baking powder, flour and salt; add to mixture.
Mix in oatmeal, Post Toasties, coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Use 1/4-cup measuring cup to drop cookies, 6 cookies to sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 15 minutes, until light brown.

title: chocolate chess pie *
directions: Sift sugar, cocoa and flour together.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and margarine.
Bake in uncooked pie shell.
Oven temperature: 350°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese in order given.
Pour half of the mixture into hot, well-greased iron skillet.
Sprinkle half of the cheese over batter. Add remaining corn meal mixture and top with the rest of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bread may be sliced and buttered, if so desired.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook fettucini according to package directions.
Drain well and return to pot.
Add butter or margarine, milk, grated cheese and parsley.
Toss until fettucini is well coated.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve.

title: golden cauliflower au gratin
directions: Saute onions in 4 tablespoons butter until soft.
Add flour and water to make white sauce.
Blend in cauliflower and cheese.
Add eggs and mix until blended.
Put into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with breadcrumbs, parsley and 2 tablespoons butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bucks harbor clam dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a small flat casserole. Mix all ingredients together, place in casserole and bake for 30 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken cordon bleu casserole
directions: Cut chicken and ham into chunks, place into the bottom of a 13 x 9 pan.
Saute onion in margarine, add flour to make paste, slowly add cream and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute stirring constantly, add dry mustard and pour over chicken and ham.
Top with cheese, breadcrumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy apple pie
directions: In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour over apples and mix.
Put in pie shell.
Place sliced margarine over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Chop dried beef and onions very fine.
Mix about 3/4 of chopped beef in cream cheese.
Add onions, Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into a ball and roll into remaining beef.

title: hawaiian chiffon salad
directions: Mix gelatin with boiling water; stir until dissolved.

Add frozen orange juice to hot mixture; chill until partially set. Add pineapple and mandarins; place in 9 x 13-inch pan until stiff. Follow directions on chiffon pie mix; add prepared Dream Whip. Spread mixture over top of congealed gelatin mixture. Refrigerate.
Spread grated Cheddar cheese evenly over top before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: honey nut granola
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all the ingredients except the raisins. Mix well.
Bake ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in raisins.
Spread onto ungreased sheet to cool.
Store in dry place or better yet, refrigerate.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Melt margarine, then add the peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and spread over first layer.
Chill about one hour.
Cut into squares.
Best if stored in refrigerator.

title: raspberry squares
directions: Mix flour with sugar and salt.
Cut in Crisco or oleo until it looks like coarse meal.
Add well beaten egg.
Mix until blended. Chill slightly.
Press 3/4 of mixture in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread on jam and nuts.
Top with remaining crumb mixture. Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in cake mix (dry), cherry pie filling and oil until blended.
Spread in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean (surface of cake will be bumpy). Cool completely.

title: mushroom-tomato salad
directions: Mix vinegar, olive oil, vegetable oil, sugar, basil, salt and garlic in tightly covered container.
Pour over mushrooms in glass or plastic bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours and not over 24 hours.
Arrange tomato slices on lettuce leaves.
Spoon mushrooms on tomatoes.

title: tomato tart
directions: Arrange the tomatoes slices evenly in the pie shell. Cover with the cheese. Sprinkle with basil. Drizzle with olive oil. Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: date candy roll
directions: Cook sugar and milk until forms soft ball in cold water. Remove and cool without stirring.
Beat in dates; add pecans and beat until almost hard.
Shape in roll in damp cloth and put in refrigerator.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Punch hole in bag of Doritos and crush.
Put a layer of chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Simmer all other ingredients for 15 minutes.
Pour over chips.
Put rest of the chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french onion soup(with beef)
directions: Saute onions.
Add water.
Add beef bouillon cubes, Worcestershire sauce and beef chunks.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Pour over French bread in ovenware bowls.
Top with Monterey Jack or Mozzarella cheese.
Put bowls in microwave to melt cheese.

title: blintz souffle
directions: Melt butter or oleo in
9 x 12-inch baking dish and put blintzes in it.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
(Sprinkle with cinnamon, optional.)
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or
1 hour if blintzes are frozen.
Excellent for a brunch.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: canned green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes and set aside.
Bring a large pot of water to boiling.
Sterilize canning jars and lids.
I use a wire basket for putting tomatoes in the boiling water and put enough to fill one jar at a time.
Let tomatoes stay in boiling water ONLY long enough for them to change color, no more than 3 to 5 minutes.
Put into hot jar being sure to layer enough to fill jar.
Pour hot liquid from cooking pot over tomatoes and put a knife tip of citric acid in each jar.
Seal.
You may want to keep an extra small pot of boiling water in case the large pot gets too low on water.

title: pierogi lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; put aside.
Mash potatoes and add cheese to potatoes; beat, using a mixer.
Add sour cream.
Saute onions in margarine until soft.
Add half of onions to potato mixture as well as bacon, salt and pepper.
Place layer of noodles in 9 x 13-inch pan, then a layer of potato mixture.
Repeat, ending with noodles.
Top with remaining onions and margarine.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until heated through, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: putters pizza
directions: Cut up tomatoes; add 2 slices ham and 1 slice cheese.
Put on brown bread with mayonnaise.

title: apple pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry dough.
Fill with apples (if fresh apples, peel and quarter; simmer in 1/4 cup water until tender).
Combine remaining ingredients, except butter.
Sprinkle over apples; dot with butter.

title: fisherman's chowder
directions: Skin and bone fish.
Cut into 2 or 3 pieces.
In a 4-quart pan, saute onions with 1/4 cup oleo until golden.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add potatoes, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and boiling water; stir well.
Arrange fish on top.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add milk and 3 tablespoons butter and heat.
Do not boil.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan or cookie sheet; use a little flour.
Bake for whatever directions call for on dough roll. Cool.
Mix with mixer cream cheese, Cool Whip,
sugar and vanilla. Spread on cooled dough.
Cut in squares.
On each square, add one fruit.
Keep refrigerated until served.

title: peach pudding surprise
directions: Combine cold cooked rice, coconut, peaches and pineapple. Stir together condensed milk and lemon juice.
Combine milk mixture and rice mixture.
Add vanilla, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour into an 8 x 11 1/2-inch buttered Pyrex dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then add pumpkin, eggs, raisins, nuts and oil.
Mix well.
Bake in 3 greased loaf pans at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown the ground beef and let it drain.
Cut the Velveeta cheese into chunks and put into a crock-pot.
Add the drained ground beef and the salsa.
Add anything else you are going to put in the dip.
Turn the crock-pot on high until the cheese is melted, then turn it down on low.
Be sure to stir the cheese while it is melting.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil whole potatoes until soft; let cool.
Peel hard-boiled eggs.
In large bowl, cut potatoes into chunks.
Chop eggs fine and shred the cheese.
Add pickles and 2 to 3 dashes of salt, then stir in mayonnaise gradually, until stirred well and moist.

title: reuben meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, catsup and salt in bowl, mixing lightly.
Combine sauerkraut, 3/4 cup of the Swiss cheese, pastrami, sour cream and mustard.
Pat out 1/3 of the meat mixture on baking dish, then spread 1/2 of sauerkraut mixture. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, loosely covered with foil.
Remove tent.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top of loaf and bake 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream together the peanut butter and butter.
Gradually add sugars, beating well after each addition.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add vanilla.
Gradually mix in flour, baking powder and salt, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Let cool completely and frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: texas millionaire candy
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 cup milk.
Stir well and let come to a good boil, stirring well, then add other cup of milk slowly (do not stop boil).
Cook until it forms soft ball in cold water. Add 1 pound whole pecans.
Pour into large buttered pan and place in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in squares.
Dip in chocolate dip.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: macaroni picnic salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Combine and mix salad dressing or mayonnaise, mustard, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Pour over macaroni mixture.
Add eggs and mix well.
Cover and chill several hours.
Serve on crisp salad greens, if desired and garnish with the crumbled bacon.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: red hot christmas wreaths
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Empty both mix pouches into bowl.
Add egg, water and 3 to 4 drops green food coloring.
Mix well.
Form dough in 3/8-inch ropes. Cut in 4-inch pieces.
Shape into wreaths on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart. Decorate with candied cherry pieces or red hots.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes. Cool 1 minute. Remove from cookie sheet with spatula.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: texas sheet cake and frosting
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa.
Blend in sugar, plain flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Pour boiling mixture over dry mixture.
Add eggs, sour cream and soda and beat well. Pour in well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter over very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Stir in cereal.
Press half the mixture into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill.
Set remaining mixture aside.
Melt chocolate chips, sugar, butter and water in double boiler (over hot, not boiling, water).
Stir constantly until smooth.
Spread over chilled cereal mixture.
Spread remaining cereal mixture evenly over top, pressing it in gently. Chill until firm (approximately 1 hour).

title: venezuelan quesillo
directions: Caramelize sugar.
Beat together eggs, milk, vanilla and sugar. Bake for 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Uncover last 10 minutes. Refrigerate.
Serve with small cups of strong black coffee.
One recipe makes small Corning Ware dish.
I usually double recipe.

title: monster cookies for a crowd
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and syrup.
Add all other ingredients.
You may need to mix these in a dishpan or roaster using your hands. Use ice cream scoop to make Monster Cookies; flatten gently with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Great for a bazaar! May also use teaspoon and make regular size cookies.

title: cheese dream sandwiches
directions: Grate cheese and all ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate. To prepare rolled sandwiches, flatten one slice of trimmed bread with rolling pin.
Spread with filling.
Roll from one corner of bread to the other.
Fasten with a toothpick.
Chill rolls.
Brush with melted margarine and toast just before serving.
Makes 70 sandwiches.
Freezes well.
Delicious.

title: corn and crawfish soup
directions: Blend together margarine and flour over low heat.
Add onion; saute until wilted.
Add remaining ingredients, except grated cheese and shallots.
Cook on medium heat for 40 minutes.
Add shallots to soup just before serving.
Add grated cheese to individual bowls.
Serves 7 to 8.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well together.
Press into tins lined with foil.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 weeks before serving and eating.
Makes great Christmas presents.

title: granulated soap
directions: Add the lye, ammonia and Borax to the water; mix carefully. Gradually add the grease, stirring all the while.
Stir about 15 minutes, then stir off and on for 2 days until dry and granulated. The more this is stirred, the finer the grain.
Store in a plastic container.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in greased (with butter) 10 x 1 1/2-inch quiche dish.
Beat until smooth the next 5 ingredients, by hand, about 1 minute.
Pour into dish containing first ingredients.
Bake in preheated oven at 400°
for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: honey cinnamon apples
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cook over medium-low heat until apples are soft.
These are great with pork chops cooked on grill.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in baking dish. Chill overnight.
Melt 1/2 stick butter or margarine.
Mix with 1 cup crushed Cheese Tid-Bits.
Spread over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: garden fresh turkey stir-fry
directions: In a plastic bag, combine salt, pepper, garlic powder and paprika; mix well.
Add turkey strips and coat with seasonings. In a skillet (or wok), heat 2 tablespoons oil; stir-fry turkey 3 to 4 minutes or until no longer pink inside.
Remove from skillet; keep warm.
Add remaining oil, yellow peppers, green peppers and snow peas.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning. Reduce heat and cook 2 minutes until vegetables are tender and crisp.
Add turkey and tomatoes.
Heat 2 minutes longer until warm through.

title: pizza topper(microwave)
directions: Spread each muffin half with pizza sauce.
Top each with 3 slices pepperoni and then with cheese.
Place halves on microproof plate. Cook on 60 for 45 to 60 seconds or until cheese is melted. Let stand 2 minutes before serving.

title: apricot delight
directions: Tear cake into pieces and put in pan or large bowl.
Combine apricot nectar, sugar, lemon juice and cornstarch and cook until thick.
Let cool slightly, then pour over cake pieces.
Cool completely.
Cover with Dream Whip topping and sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pasta
directions: Mix eggs, water, salt and oil together. Make well in flour and add egg mixture. Mix into flour and knead dough briefly. Cover with warm
towel and let stand 15 minutes. Roll out and cut into strips or use pasta machine. Boil in salted water.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and butter in large bowl.
Stir in sour cream, soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over top. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients for filling together, adding pecans last. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer, until set.

title: pat-pats cookies
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Stir in the next 4 ingredients until thick.
Add the last 3 ingredients; mix well.
Dough will be soft. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Take glass with sugar on and stamp each cookie.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: 7-up party salad
directions: Combine 7-Up and marshmallows in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until marshmallows are melted.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Add hot mixture slowly to cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill until partly set.
Fold in sour cream and mayonnaise. Blend thoroughly.
Pour into a lightly oiled 2-quart mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: memphis chili
directions: Brown meat in a
large, heavy saucepan.
Drain off fat. Add all of the remaining ingredients and heat to boil.	Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mama's chick-n-dressin'
directions: Cornbread can be made 1 day ahead and chicken can be cooked 1 day ahead, also.

title: squash pickles
directions: Slice squash and onions very thin.
Shred peppers and garlic. Mix lightly and sprinkle salt over all.
Put in large pan and cover with ice cubes.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients together and heat in large pot.
When hot, add vegetables and stir occasionally.
Heat until scalded through but do not boil.
Pack in jars while hot and seal.
Delicious and crunchy.
Yields 7 to 9 pints.

title: janet's beet relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Place in hot, sterilized jars.
Seal in screw top jars.

title: 5 layer pudding recipe(mud slide)
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients and press in bottom of pan; bake about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate covered eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into eggs.
Coat with chocolate when eggs are cold and firm.
After dipping in chocolate, eggs may be decorated with cherries, frosting, nuts, coconut, etc.

title: peanut butter bread sticks
directions: Remove crust from bread slices.
Cut bread into sticks and make bread crumbs from crust.
Toast bread sticks one and a half hours in 250° oven.
Combine salad oil, peanut butter and sugar. Dip sticks into peanut butter mixture and roll in bread crumbs.

title: apple crumb pie(fast and easy)
directions: Pare apples; cut into eighths and put into a bowl with a tight fitting lid.
Mix your 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon together and pour over apples in bowl.
Seal your lid on bowl and shake to coat apples.
Pour this mixture into your pie shell.

title: bananas foster
directions: In 1 1/2-quart glass bowl, combine brown sugar, butter, water, lemon juice, rum extract and nutmeg.
Cook on High for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes; stir twice.
Add bananas and stir gently.
Cook at Medium for 1 minute.
Spoon warm bananas and sauce into dessert dishes. Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: warm dove chocolate cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In the top of double boiler over hot water, combine Dove Promises dark chocolate, butter and sugar until just melted.
Add eggs and whisk until well combined; add flour and mix. Lightly grease four 4 oz. custard cups, muffin molds or ramekins with baking spray or butter.
Distribute batter evenly among the four molds.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels in microwave with milk. Add pecans. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam. Cool in refrigerator. Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler. Dip caramels.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, flour, soda, buttermilk, bananas, salt and nuts.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Fill with mixture and bake for 1 hour at 300° to 325°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and form into ball.
Roll in 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake for 30 minutes at 375° in a casserole dish that has been sprayed with vegetable cooking spray. Remove from oven; top with shredded or grated cheese.
Return to oven; bake for 10 minutes.
Great!!!

title: old-fashioned cabbage
directions: Cut slice from top of cabbage; cut out inside of cabbage, leaving 3/4-inch shell.
Reserve inside of cabbage for cole slaw. Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir ground beef in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until light brown.
Drain.
Stir in 1/2 cup of tomato sauce, the whole tomatoes with liquid, stuffing mix, onion, garlic and salt.
Break up tomatoes.
Fill cabbage shell with mixture.
Place in Dutch oven.
Mix remaining sauce and water. Pour around cabbage and bake for about 45 minutes.
Remove cabbage and cut into 6 wedges.
Spoon hot tomato sauce over.

title: angel hair pasta with chicken
directions: Heat 1 tbsp of oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from skillet and drain on paper towels.
Heat remaining oil in same skillet.
Begin heating water for pasta.
Add carrots to skillet.
Cook for 4 minutes, stirring.
Add broccoli and garlic to skillet.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
While pasta is cooking, add chicken broth and basil to skillet.
Stir to combine.
Reduce heat and let simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain pasta.
Place in large serving bowl.
Top with chicken and vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: easy popovers
directions: Using a whisk or fork, combine eggs and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients, disregarding lumps.
Fill well-greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Place in a cold oven and set temperature at 450°.
Bake approximately 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except broccoli; add it last. Prepare an iron skillet or 13 x 9-inch baking dish by greasing well.
Bake in skillet for 25 to 30 minutes or in a baking dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
You can also spoon into muffin pans.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Any vegetables can be used such as cauliflower, green beans, peas or add all combined.

title: single pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in a mixing bowl.
Cut in Crisco with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture is uniform.
Sprinkle with water, 1 tablespoon at a time; toss lightly with fork.
Form into a ball.
Roll out dough on floured surface to a circle 1/8-inch thick and about 1 1/2-inches larger than inverted plate.
Ease dough into pie pan.
Trim and flute edges.

title: broiled fish with lemon and thyme
directions: Squeeze 1/2 cup juice from the lemons.
Combine the juice, salt, pepper and thyme in a glass baking dish or shallow stainless pan.
Add the fish and turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes, turning 2 or 3 times.
Heat the broiler and melt the butter.
Drain the fish.
Brush with butter and broil on both sides until opaque throughout, about 10 minutes in all.

title: sun-maid lattice raisin pie
directions: Simmer raisins in water 5 minutes.
Combine beaten eggs, sugar and salt.
Gradually add to hot raisins.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in butter, vanilla and walnuts. Cool slightly.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Cover with pastry strips, arranged lattice fashion.
Bake in very hot oven, 450°, for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: sylvia's fruit cake
directions: Mix flour and fruit.
Break in eggs.
Add milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with heavy-duty foil or 13 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Then at 200° for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer rhubarb, sugar, Jell-O and cake mix (in order - do not mix).
Dot with butter and pour water on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sue's pound cake
directions: Cream the first three ingredients together with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk and lemon and vanilla flavorings.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: cheesy egg burritos
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over low heat.
Mix eggs and milk. Pour into skillet. Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until eggs begin to set.
Add cheese spread.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until cheese spread is melted and eggs are set. Fill tortillas with eggs, lettuce and tomato.
Roll up.
Serve with salsa.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wild rice
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Add onion, rice and oregano.
Cook on top of stove until slightly brown.
Add beef consomme and water.
Add salt to taste and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° until fluffy.

title: bif casserole
directions: Grind Bif, cheese and onion.
Add other ingredients; bake until bubbly.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except corn flake crumbs.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Parboil and drain frozen peas.
Cut up celery, onions and green pepper.
Add to chilled peas.
Mix in enough Miracle Whip to make salad creamy.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Rub surface of chicken with vegetable oil; bake for 25 minutes at 375°. Set aside to cool. Melt butter; saut onion and celery 4 to 5 minutes in large saucepan. Dice chicken and add it to other ingredients, except noodles. Boil, then reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes until carrots are soft. Add noodles and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve with a pinch of parsley.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix
cabbage
and
onion
together
in large container. Bring to a boil the vinegar, celery seed and mustard.
Add oil and sugar and bring to a second boil.
Pour this over cabbage. Let
stand (covered)
outside
refrigerator
overnight.
Next morning, refrigerate.
Keeps for weeks.
Great with barbecue.

title: party rice
directions: Bring chicken broth and orange juice to a boil.
Stir in rice. Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Saute green onions, mushrooms and red pepper in margarine for 5 minutes.
Add to cooked rice along with the garlic powder.

title: black bean chili
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight.
Drain and rinse beans.
Combine beans and one quart water in large pan or with enough water to cover beans.
Heat to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours or until tender.
Cut beef into 1/4 to 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat oil in pan, add meat, green peppers, onions, jalapeno peppers and garlic. Cook until tender.
Reduce heat to low; add chile powder, cumin, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Simmer one hour.
Drain beans, add to pan with other ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.
Makes 6 servings.
Even better when made one day and reheated the next.

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Saute onions, celery and mushrooms in butter along with poultry seasoning until onions are just tender.
Add chicken and noodles.
Cover with water and add soup and bouillon cubes.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Correct seasoning by adding salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 8.

title: marti's corn soup
directions: Fry finely diced bacon until crisp. Add onion and saut until soft. Add corn to onion and bacon. Cook until it begins to brown. Add milk, salt and pepper. Cook until thickened, then add cream (or canned milk) and heat until smooth. Serves 6.

title: ham and swiss on noodles
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Set aside and keep warm.
Saute green onion in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add mushrooms and peas and cook until heated.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Melt remaining margarine in pan; add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Add cheese and stir until smooth.
Add vegetables, ham and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Cook until heated thoroughly.
Serve over noodles.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix
and
bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with 1/2 cup chopped
nuts, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 3/4 cup butter.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Wash and drain the chicken wings.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 30 minutes.
Beat the eggs.
Dip chicken in eggs; roll in flour.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Put chicken in a baking dish; pour sauce over chicken.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° to 375° oven.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Melt butter in double boiler; add mushroom soup, salt, pepper and mustard.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Whip the cream.
Add mushrooms, shrimp and sherry; continue to cook over low heat.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Fold in cream.
If sauce is too thick, you may add milk. To be served over rice, in pastry shell or over toast.
Serves 8.

title: cheese puffs
directions: In top of large double boiler, over simmering water, melt the butter and cheese together, stirring with a wire whisk.
Blend in Worcestershire sauce, onion and cayenne.
With electric beater, thoroughly beat in the eggs.
Turn off heat.
Carefully dip each bread cube into the cheese mixture.
Turn to coat thoroughly. Shake off excess mixture.
Place cubes on cookie sheet and freeze. After cubes are frozen, store in airtight containers.
Place cubes on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Serve immediately.
Makes 40 to 45 cubes.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Sear beef (brown rapidly on both sides to hold juice).
Place level tablespoon of flour in browning bag and shake well.
Place meat in bag.
Mix 2 cans of soup with 1 can of water.
Stir into the soup sliced carrots, onion and celery.
Pour mixture over the roast and tie the bag.
Puncture about 3 times with a 2-tined fork (allow steam to escape).
Place in 325° oven and bake 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.
Gravy is in the bag.

title: squash casserole(a dessert)
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Parboil squash in small amount of water.
Scoop pulp out.
Place in bowl; add remaining ingredients, except cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes (425° if using glass dish).

title: swordfish marinade
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour over fillets of swordfish and marinate for 4 to 6 hours.
Grill for 8 minutes each side.

title: roemayne's lasagne
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
In blender, combine cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Mix with 2 cups of grated cheese.
Reserve remaining cheese for top.

title: sugar snap peas
directions: Core red pepper and cut into strips about 1/2-inch wide and 2-inches long.
Heat oil in heavy, medium pan over medium heat. Add pepper strips and saute until nearly tender, 4 or 5 minutes. Add sugar snap peas, garlic, and thyme and toss over heat for a few seconds.
Add water and cook, tightly covered, over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until peas are tender-crisp, about 3 minutes.
If excess water remains in pan, uncover and cook until it evaporates.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer 1/2 chips, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 onion and 1/2 cheese. Combine soups and broth; put 1/2 of this mixture over first layer. Add second layer of chips, chicken, onion and cheese, followed by remaining liquid mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cookies for health conscious
directions: Combine flour and next 3 ingredients.
Gradually add margarine, sugars, egg substitute and vanilla.
Stir in raisins. Spray cookie sheet.
Drop dough by spoonfuls and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Layer
coconut and chopped nuts in bottom of sheet cake pan. Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions on box
and pour mix over bottom layer.
Take stick of margarine and
cream cheese
and heat in microwave until softened.
Add powdered sugar to this and pour as evenly as possible over top of
cake mix. Bake at 350° or temperature on cake box, adding 5 minutes baking time for mixture.

title: christmas strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add all other ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour half of the mixture into long dish and let congeal. Spread sour cream over it.
Add the other half of the jello mixture and let it congeal.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix lettuce and onions.
In a skillet, brown in butter, almonds, sesame seed and broken up noodles over low heat.
Add to lettuce and onions.

title: herbed potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions together until potatoes are tender. Drain and reserve water.
Put potatoes through a ricer or coarse strainer.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray
pizza
pan
with Pam.
Prepare Duncan Hines sugar cookie mix as directed on box.
Spread on pizza pan and bake at 350° until brown; let cool.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Crumble beef into a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add onion.
Cook over medium heat 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Simmer covered 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: tennessee buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat
oven
Mix flour and shortening.
Add just enough
buttermilk until dough leaves side of bowl.
Too much milk
makes
dough sticky and difficult to handle, while too little
milk makes biscuits dry.
Knead dough on a floured surface.
Roll dough and cut out biscuits.
Best to roll dough about
inch
thick
before cutting.
Bake on an ungreased baking sheet,
almost touching, at 500° for 8 to 10 minutes or until top is golden brown.
You may wish to dip cut dough into melted butter prior to baking.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in vanilla ice cream and pineapple.
Chill until partially thickened.
Stir and pour into baked, cooled pie crust.
Chill until firm.

title: rhapsody pie
directions: Bake pie crusts first.
Mix all other ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Prepare instant potatoes according to directions on box.
Place hamburger into baking dish.
Drain corn, then place corn on top of the hamburger.
Next, put the instant potatoes on the top.
You may garnish with cheese, if desired.
Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 30 minutes. Delicious and fast.

title: broccoli and stove top
directions: Cook and drain frozen broccoli.
Mix together broccoli, mushroom soup, mayonnaise, onion and 2 eggs.
Add Cheddar cheese soup, Stove Top and melted butter.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: devil's delight
directions: Mix and press flour, melted butter and pecans into an oblong baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin muffins
directions: Mix oats, flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add oleo and cut in with a pastry blender.
Stir in raisins.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir until ingredients are moistened.
Fill 12 medium sized paper lined muffin cups.
Sprinkle with topping. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: granny's squash and tomato casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender, drain and set aside.
Melt butter and blend in flour, tomatoes, pepper, onion and egg.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Simmer for five minutes.
Put squash into buttered dish (9 x 13-inch).
Pour tomato mixture over squash and sprinkle cracker (or bread) crumbs over top.
Add grated cheese for topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin orange segments.
Place in mixing bowl.
Add coconut and pecan pieces.
Fold in sour cream.
Start with 8 ounces of sour cream.
Add more sour cream to your liking or taste.
Refrigerate 4 to 8 hours.

title: raisin walnut bits
directions: In a large bowl, mix the first 6 ingredients.
In small bowl, mix buttermilk, oil and egg, then stir into flour mixture until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Cut loaf lengthwise into thirds, then crosswise into eighths.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Combine syrup and sugar in saucepan.
Place over medium heat.
Heat until bubbles (do not overcook). Stir constantly. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter. Stir until smooth. Add cereal. Stir until coated.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Cool.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes in a loaf pan.
Glaze with powdered sugar and water.

title: baked cheese and rice casserole
directions: Butter a long casserole dish.
Partially cook and drain the broccoli thoroughly, then place in buttered dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Cover chicken with ham.
Mix the next 5 ingredients and spread over the casserole.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until casserole bubbles, approximately 20 minutes.

title: blender banana cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Whirl fully ripe bananas in blender.
Add oil and eggs; whirl until well blended.
Place flour, sugar, baking soda and salt into a medium size bowl.
Pour banana mixture into dry ingredients and mix until blended. Pour into pan; rap on table to remove any large bubbles. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.

title: potato soup
directions: Saut celery and onion in margarine in large Dutch oven until tender.
Add next 8 ingredients; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Mash vegetables.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese is melted.

title: yummy peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and margarine; add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Combine flour, salt, and baking soda in a large bowl. Add dry ingredients, a little at a time, to creamed mixture. Dough will be very soft. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet; flatten with a fork dipped in sugar. Bake about 10 minutes at 350°. Yields about 30 dozen.

title: any flavor cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Be sure the pan is greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, checking every few minutes until done.

title: roman bake
directions: Brown meat; drain and add all other ingredients (except noodles and cheese) and cook until well mixed.
Put noodles in 12 x 9-inch
pan; pour meat mixture over top of noodles.
Top with cheese.
Cover and put in oven.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes, covered.

title: fresh apple cake
