directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Add flour and beat well.
Fold in apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 3 pans.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Grind vegetables using coarse blade.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.

title: mexicorn dip
directions: Mix well and serve with corn chips.

title: bonsaint family meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Place on baking pan about 1-inch from each other.
Brown in 350° oven approximately 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and place in crock-pot with spaghetti sauce.
Let simmer in sauce about 1 hour before eating. Makes about 25 meatballs.

title: cheesy baked potatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
A 13 x 9-inch pan works well.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: russian herring salad
directions: In a bowl, mix herring, potatoes, apples, beets, pickles, cucumber, eggs, sour cream and mustard.
Stir until well blended. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Line a salad bowl with lettuce leaves and spoon in salad mixture.
Garnish with egg slices.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: pudding pie or coconut pie
directions: Put eggs into a frying pan.
Beat eggs in pan.
Add 1 cup milk and mix well.
Mix sugar and flour together in another bowl.
Add to the egg and milk mixture.
Put in salt.
Add the other cup of milk and the vanilla.
Cook on burner medium heat and stir constantly until thickened.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Add 1/2 cup coconut if you want coconut pie.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar together until smooth.
Stir in a small amount of the pineapple-orange juice and mix until smooth.
Add the egg and beat well (with spoon).
Add the rest of the pineapple juice while stirring, then add the butter.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture comes to a boil, remove from the heat and cool.
After cooled, fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over Jell-O.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.

title: quick cajun catfish
directions: Place fillets in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with Cajun and lemon pepper seasonings.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until fish flakes easily with fork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and combine with corn meal.
Mix eggs and milk; add with shortening.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased shallow pan and bake in a moderate oven (450°) for about 20 minutes.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Combine all but last ingredient, pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes or potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together.
Spray casserole pan with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Drain and set aside.
Make or use frozen pie crust.
Bake according to recipe.

title: beef ball
directions: Chop dried beef in blender.
Set a small amount aside.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a ball.
Roll in chopped beef.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs; mix together. Sift together cocoa, flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk, boiling water and vanilla.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pronto pizza deluxe(6 servings)
directions: Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium high heat.
Add leeks and bell peppers; saute until just tender, about 8 minutes. Add crushed red pepper; stir for 30 seconds.
Transfer to plate. Add sausage to skillet; cook until no longer pink, crumbling with fork, about 4 minutes.
Transfer to another plate.

title: henry's rolady(spanelske ptacky)
directions: Season thin slices of round steak with salt and pepper.
Put slice of onion, slice of bacon and a pickle slice on meat.
Roll and tie with thin string (thread or dental floss).
Fry onion until soft.
Remove onion to platter.
Fry rolled steak quickly on both sides.
Lower heat, add onions and 1/2 cup water and simmer until done.
Thicken gravy with flour.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Heat milk to just below boiling; let cool to wrist temperature (neither hot, nor cool on your wrist).
Stir in flour with a wooden spoon (not metal).
Gently fold in Starter from previous batch.
Let mixture sit in a warm place overnight.
Use in Sourdough Waffles or in many other recipes.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Wash, peel and cut potatoes into cubes.
Cover potatoes with water in saucepan.
Chop onion and add to potatoes.
Cook until tender.

title: garden salad
directions: Heat oil, vinegar and sugar in pan and boil.
Cool mixture. Add salt and pepper and pour over drained vegetables.
Refrigerate, will keep for several days.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until tender. Drain and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour in a greased baking dish.
Mix stuffing mix, margarine and cheese.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zieh kuechla
directions: Combine water, yeast and sugar.
Add salt and 2 cups flour. Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer or rotary beater.
Add eggs and shortening.
Beat for 1 minute.
Blend in 4 1/2 cups sifted flour and stir until dough is formed.
Let rest for 20 minutes.
This makes dough easier to handle.

title: snicker pie
directions: Soften ice cream to stirring stage.
Mix with pudding and peanut butter. Fold in cool whip.
Pour into crust and freeze. Let sit out 10 minutes before serving.

title: classy gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Stir well; cover and chill 8 hours.
Ladle into serving bowl; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Yield:
About 2 quarts.

title: easy vegetable meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pack in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: spicy yogurt sauce
directions: Combine yogurt, pimiento, coriander, cumin, salt and pepper in blender or food processor.
Puree until smooth.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: cocktail sauce for seafood
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill sauce and seafood before serving. Will keep for a long time in the refrigerator.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix together in a large bowl: pudding mix, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Beat until smooth.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mash cranberry sauce with fork; add lemon juice and blend. Pour into 1-quart bowl with lid.
In another bowl, add sugar to softened cream cheese and mayonnaise; mix well.
Add pecans.
Whip cream and fold into this mixture.
Spoon this mixture over cranberry sauce and freeze until firm.
To serve, cut into wedges and put on lettuce leaf.
Good with turkey and dressing.
Makes 3 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together; let set overnight in refrigerator.
Good with all finger vegetables.

title: ice cream cone cake
directions: You will need aluminum foil, in strips 9 inches wide by 9 1/2 inches long (one per cone).

title: colossal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a huge bowl or cook pot, beat together margarine and sugars.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Stir in oatmeal, chocolate chips and baking soda, mixing well.
Drop by 1/4 cupful on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork to 2 1/2-inch diameter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing from pan.

title: hot potato salad for 100
directions: In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp; remove to paper towels to drain.
Add flour to drippings; cook and stir until bubbly.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Add the boiling water to the jello, mixing well, and refrigerate until slightly thickened.
In large mixing bowl, whip the chilled milk and add lemon juice, rind and sugar.
Fold the thickened jello into the milk mixture.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish with 3/4 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Pour the jello mixture into this.
Sprinkle the rest of the crumbs over the top. Store in the refrigerator.

title: baked white onions with sour cream
directions: Bake the onions in the oven at 350° until fork-tender.
Let the onions cool and peel them.
Place the onions in a Corning dish and let them get hot again. Stir together sour cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over the onions.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, cream cheese, horseradish, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and pepper juice.
Mix well.
Stir in Cheddar cheese and crab.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Sprinkle with paprika. Serve with crackers.
Makes 20 servings.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Melt oleo.
Add eggs and mix.
Add sugar, flour, water and vinegar.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Add mayo and mustard.

title: monster cookies
directions: Using the largest bowl you own, mix ingredients together in the order listed (dough will be crumbly). Use an ice cream scoop to drop dough onto a cookie sheet (6 to 9 cookies per sheet). Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.

title: chicken creole
directions: In 2 quart saucepan saute onion, green pepper and celery in the butter until onion is tender but not browned. Add mushrooms, tomatoes, bay leaf, sugar, seasoned salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to a boil. Simmer, uncovered for 10 minutes. Add chicken and heat. Blend cornstarch and water and stir into mixture. Cook, stirring until thickened. Add parsley, and salt to taste. Serve on hot cooked rice. Good served with a green salad.

title: taquitos de pobre
directions: Peel, cut up potatoes and boil (as in making mashed potatoes, using a little less water).
When soft, drain water; add margarine and salt to taste.
Smash until fluffy.
Warm corn tortillas; add 1 tablespoon potatoes and roll into taquitos.
Fry in oil until desired crispness.
Spread a thin layer of mayonnaise and top with cabbage and Parmesan cheese.
Delicious!

title: pork hash rolled in eggs
directions: Chop
green onion; use more white.
Add to ground pork. Grate ginger
and mix.
Add shoyu, sake, sugar, ajinomoto and eggs; mix
again.
Fry
eggs;
cool.
Spread
pork
on
eggs evenly; roll it from
sides.
Steam for about 5 minutes on high heat and 20 minutes on low heat.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Saute or brown the onions and pepper a little, then add the mushroom soup.
Add the mushroom pieces and sour cream.
Simmer a little, then add cut up chicken.
Stir in enough cornstarch so it will spread nicely.

title: grapefruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Heat reserved grapefruit juice and enough water to make 1 3/4 cups.
Add to gelatine mixture.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add fruits, celery and nuts.
Put in a ring or mold previously rinsed in cold water and it will set in about 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Wash and trim cauliflower, leaving it whole.
Cook in water with salt added, about 15 minutes.
Drain.
Place in shallow dish. Frost with mayonnaise and mustard mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 10 minutes at 350°
until cheese melts.
Easy and delicious.

title: divinity cupcakes
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together in bowl.
Melt shortening and cool.
Add shortening and buttermilk to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 2 more minutes.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: crab cake
directions: Mix ingredients and add crab meat last.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes on each side.
Makes 12 cakes.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Grind meat and onion together.
Mix all other ingredients together and blend thoroughly with meat and onions.
Tastes good on rye bread.

title: plum bread
directions: Mix baby food, sugar, oil, eggs and food coloring.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: grandma's baked chicken
directions: Coat chicken pieces with sour cream.
Mix the dry ingredients and spread on a plate.
Roll chicken on the plate thoroughly coating with dry ingredients.
Place in a greased pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake 15 to 30 minutes more, until done.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: In a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan, layer half the dry bread cubes.
Combine applesauce mixture over bread cubes.
Layer remaining bread cubes atop, dot with butter.
Combine milk, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Pour over bread mixture.
Lightly sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until knife inserted just off center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grilled marinated swordfish
directions: Combine oil, lemon juice, garlic, basil, oregano, salt and pepper; mix well.
Brush both sides of fish generously with mixture and refrigerate in marinade for 2 hours.
Turn steaks every half hour to marinate thoroughly.
Grill about 6 inches from coals for 5 minutes; turn and baste and cook 6 or 7 minutes more. Serve steaks brushed generously with melted butter and topped with fresh parsley.
Serves 6.

title: heavenly hash pie (date-pecan pie)
directions: Beat sugar, flour and egg.
Fold in dates, cream and pecans. Pour in pie shell and bake 1 hour at 300°.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: hot stuff
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add chili powder and red pepper.
Add beans, water and tomatoes.
Simmer until heated through.
Serve with warm tortillas.
Serves 5 to 6. Decrease chili powder and pepper for not so hot stuff!

title: dump cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cottage cheese roast
directions: Mix ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
May use onion and chicken seasoning as desired with the other seasonings for desired taste.

title: dale's mom's bars
directions: Boil syrup and sugar.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Put mixture in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chips and pour and spread over top of mixture.
Chill until top is firm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix by hand with a big spoon until ingredients are blended.
Pour in a prepared 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Add Cream Cheese Icing.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine.
Mix vegetables, crawfish, soup, rice and seasonings well.
Place in a 2 or 3-quart casserole.
Top with seasoned crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Sometimes, instead of bread crumbs, I use Durkee fried onions on top.

title: apple ring pickles
directions: Wash large cucumbers.
Peel and core out seed.
Slice cucumbers about 1/2-inch thick.
Mix cucumbers and water.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and soak in cold water 3 hours.
Drain and wash in clear water.
Mix vinegar, food coloring and alum.
Pour over cucumbers and add water to cover.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Drain. Mix vinegar, cinnamon, red hots and sugar.
Boil and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand overnight.
Bring to boil again and put in jars.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan and over medium heat, bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from stove and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour into buttered dish and let cool.

title: raspberry carousel salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add cranberry juice cocktail and chill until thickened (1 hour).
Fold in apples, celery and nuts.
Spoon into 6 cup mold and chill until set, about 15 minutes.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in remaining boiling water. Chill until slightly thickened, about 1 hour.
Combine Cool Whip and mayonnaise; fold in Jell-O (lemon).
Spoon on top of other mixture.
Chill until firm, at least 4 hours.
Unmold.
Good.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease and heat cast-iron muffin or other mold pan.
(We use corn stick.)
Combine dry ingredients. Stir in milk, oil and egg until just blended.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Cook the pineapple, sugar and flour together until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.

title: cucumber and onions
directions: Soak cucumber and onion in salted water in refrigerator for about 2 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Cover with sour cream and vinegar mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped dill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°. Grease and flour your pans.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until fluffy and light. Add vanilla and then well beaten eggs. Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Add to creamed mixture. Add oatmeal and nuts. Form dough into long rolls. Wrap in waxed paper and chill, preferably overnight. Slice into cookies and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: In large pan, brown meat and drain.
Add onions, tomatoes, beans and spices.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix this all first until it is creamy.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda with 2 cups flour.
Sift the flour and soda one time, then add 1/2 cup chopped peanuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet with a tablespoon.
Bake at 350°.

title: 3 step cheesecake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with an electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; blend thoroughly. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Will set when cool.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: beef enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain and add taco seasoning. Place 1 flour tortilla on a plate.
Spoon 2 spoons of meat and 1 spoon of refried beans into middle of each shell.
Roll up and place in dish.
Beat chili in saucepan to warm.
Pour chili over shells.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: skillet cherry tomatoes
directions: Cook and stir all ingredients in skillet until tomatoes are hot, about 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: orange pie filling
directions: Mix sugar, butter, flour and salt.
Stir in rind and juice. Add yolks and milk.
Last, add egg whites.
Makes 2 pies.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix.
Grease oblong pan and flour.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the peanut butter, shortening, sugars and egg.
After combining the flour, soda, powder and salt blend this into the creamed mixture.

title: ice cream pudding cake
directions: Crush crackers, saving 1/2 cup crumbs for top.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with crumbs.
Drizzle with melted margarine over crumbs.

title: flounder with asparagus
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender but not brown and sprinkle over fillets in equal portions.
Lay 3 asparagus spears crosswise on fillets.
Roll up carefully and spear with skewer.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Place cream cheese in medium microwave-safe mixing bowl. Microwave uncovered on High for 45 to 60 minutes or until softened. Add remaining ingredients. Mix with whisk or wooden spoon until smooth. Serve with fresh cut fruit such as strawberries, cantaloupe, pineapple chunks, grapes or bananas.

title: easy microwave stuffing
directions: Microwave butter and vegetables in covered 2-quart casserole 4 to 5 minutes on HIGH. Stir in seasonings, bouillon and egg. Add bread and toss with fork. Microwave, covered, 6 to 7 minutes at MEDIUM-HIGH, stirring twice. Fluff with fork.

title: baked spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 8.

title: louisiana fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit.
Pour pie filling over mix and chill.
Will keep for 2 weeks.
Try cherry pie filling or strawberry pie filling and add sliced peaches.
Use as a salad, dessert or serve over ice cream.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In a medium mixing bowl combine apples, celery, grapes, yogurt and walnuts; mix well.
Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours.
If desired, serve in a lettuce-lined bowl.
Yield: 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix cabbage and onion with sugar.
Boil together oil, vinegar, mustard, celery seed and sugar.
Pour over cabbage and let set overnight.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding; add oil, eggs and water.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add poppy seed and almond flavoring.
Mix well; pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rebecca's honey popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine popped corn and nuts. Set aside.

title: ham salad sandwich filling
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Prepare sandwiches.

title: corn flakes treats
directions: In a large saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Stir in condensed milk, stirring constantly (do not boil).
When hot, remove from heat and add corn flakes cereal, mixing very well. Pour with a spoon in a buttered pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: microwave pickles
directions: In a large microwave safe bowl, combine all of the ingredients.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 4 minutes; stir. Cook 3 to 4 minutes longer or until mixture is bubbly and cucumbers and onions are crisp-tender.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Serve with a slotted spoon.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ham noodle casserole
directions: Put ham and cheese
through food chopper.
Cook noodles in salted water.
Mix	all ingredients except bread crumbs and pour into baking dish.
Cover
and
place
in
moderate	oven, about 35 minutes.
Remove lid, add bread crumbs and brown.

title: swedish shrimp
directions: Saute onions in oil in nonstick skillet, to soften, for 2 minutes.
Add 3/4 cup broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp. Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, until shrimp are pink, 3 minutes.

title: watergate dessert
directions: Mix together thoroughly the dry pudding and crushed pineapple. Add whipped topping or Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Stir thoroughly and refrigerate.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef.
Add taco seasoning and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Mix mayonnaise with sour cream and spread over meat mixture. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then garnish with tomatoes.

title: pork chops with potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onion into a buttered casserole.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brown chops quickly on both sides in a little oil.
Place chops on top of the potatoes.
Blend the mushroom soup, onion soup mix and hot water.
Spread over the chops, cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 to 30 minutes more, until chops are tender and potatoes are done.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press into 9 x 13-inch pan; chill.

title: cathedral window cookies(actually aunt helen's recipe)
directions: In top of double boiler, melt margarine and chocolate chips. Add pecans and let cool several minutes, then fold in colored marshmallows. Let cool until rolls can be formed with the hands (6 rolls). Roll in flaked coconut. Refrigerate. Slice thin for serving. (YUMMY.)

title: apple dip
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Serve with apple slices and Ritz crackers.

title: pepperoni dip
directions: Chop pepperoni.
Mix with sour cream and refrigerate one day before serving.

title: triple lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients up through oil and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel onions, slice and braise in butter and oil 10 to 15 minutes.
Add paste and consomme.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add red wine.
Fill soup bowls.
Place slice of party rye on top of soup.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with Swiss cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: glazed lemon knots
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl. Mix well and set aside.

Separate roll dough into 8 rectangles; press perforations to seal. Spread about 2 teaspoons of cheese mixture over each rectangle. Roll dough, jelly roll fashion, starting at long side. Stretch dough slightly; tie in a loose knot.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Combine powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon lemon juice. Drizzle glaze over warm rolls and serve.
Yields 8 rolls.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Roll pastry.
Cut into squares 2 to 2 1/2-inches.
Make small sausage in 1 1/2-inch lengths and place in pastry squares.
Seal the squares.
Brush with egg.
Place on baking tray.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot with pork gravy or cold for snacks.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: crunchy chicken cheese bake
directions: In 3 quart oblong baking dish, place chicken.
Top with cheese.
Stir soup and spread over cheese; top with tomato. Combine margarine and stuffing; sprinkle over tomato.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve over rice.
If desired, omit tomato; combine soup with 1/4 cup milk.
Makes 8 servings.

title: turkey cheese pie
directions: Cook spinach; drain and set aside.
Combine cream cheese and butter; beat on medium speed until smooth.
Add milk; beat until smooth.
Stir in pepper, turkey and spinach.
Spoon into pie crust; cover with crust and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate decadence cake
directions: Cut chocolates and butter into small pieces.
Put in a bowl. Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar and the water in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over chocolate and butter.
Stir until melted.
Whip eggs and 1/4 cup sugar in mixer until double in size.
Stir into chocolate mixture until no white streaks appear.
Pour batter into greased paper lined 10-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° on a sheet pan with 1-inch water (as for cheesecake) for 40 to 50 minutes until cake is set.
Cool in refrigerator overnight.
To release cake, dip in hot water and run knife around edge.
Frost with whipped cream and decorate with chocolate curls.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans together; spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions; pour over first layer.
Mix melted butter with powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Mix on low speed with mixer; spread on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cloud
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, cook and stir gelatin, pudding mix and water until mixture boils, about 15 minutes. Cool until partially set; fold in whipped topping. Spoon into a bowl or individual dishes or parfait glasses. Chill until ready to serve. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: parsley rice
directions: As with any gourmet food, especially in the South, the serving of the food is as important as the preparation.

title: surprise salad
directions: In large mixing bowl combine sauerkraut, carrots, celery, green pepper, onion and pimento.
In separate bowl combine sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper; pour over sauerkraut mixture.
Toss to mix.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 4 hours before serving.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage in salted water until tender. Drain and toss with lemon juice and mustard. Serve hot.

title: mound candy bars
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, oleo, powdered sugar and vanilla together.
Press in thin layer on cookie sheet.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Cut in small squares and dip in melted chocolate with paraffin.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine soup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish. Blend well and set aside.
Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion, salt and 1/4 cup of soup mixture.
Shape into 6 patties; brown in skillet.
Drain.
Combine remaining soup mixture with 1/2 cup water and pour over patties.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Toss well.
Add sandwich spread last in mixing.
Serve with favorite crackers and drink.

title: zucchini puffs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Add the zucchini.
Heat salad oil in frying pan.
Drop by spoonful into the heated oil. Fry slowly on one side, then turn and fry second side.

title: ham dandy(servings:  8)
directions: Grease 9 x 12 x 3-inch casserole dish.
Line with bread. Scald milk; add margarine and remove from heat.
Beat eggs.
Add cheese, dry mustard and ham or bacon.
Mix with milk mixture. Pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour or nicely brown on top.

title: matt's chili beans
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: cuzzin' carl's casserole
directions: Brown meat lightly.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until lightly transparent.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Cook uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°. Turn heat down to 300°.
Cook for 30 minutes longer.

title: cheese soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot, except croutons. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Serve in warm bowls.
Top each serving with crisp croutons.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Mix sugar with melted oleo.
Add 1 egg at a time, then add syrup, flour and baking powder.
Ice cake as soon as it comes from oven.

title: texas hash
directions: Fry together pepper, onions, celery and hamburger until vegetables are tender.
Add creamed corn.
Simmer until hot through.
Serve over mashed potatoes or rice.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat.
Brown onions, garlic and green chiles.
Open can of sauce and heat.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan and put a little sauce in pan.
Dip tortillas in sauce and fill with meat and onions mixture. Place two olives and cheese.
Roll up and place seam side down in pan.
Continue until pan is full.
Put remaining sauce over all the tortilla and spread with rest of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or more.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: west virginia mountain mama mud slide
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts and pat into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until pale brown at 350°.
Cool.

title: hamburger stuffed rolls
directions: Let dough rise until doubled in size.
Meanwhile, prepare hamburgers.
Combine ground beef with remaining ingredients and shape into 16 balls.
Fry in large skillet 10 minutes, turning once.
Cool to warm on absorbent paper.
Divide dough into 16 pieces.
Flatten and shape around meat; seal seams together well. Place seam side down on greased cookie sheet.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm to cold with catsup or chili sauce.
(If served as a cold sandwich, keep refrigerated until serving time.)

title: cheesy cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave krispie treats
directions: Place butter in a 12 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
Microwave for about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on Medium-high or until melted.
Stir in marshmallows. Microwave for 1 minute on Medium-high.
Stir and continue cooking for about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on Medium-high or until marshmallows are softened.
Stir until smooth.
Mix in cereal.
Press into baking dish.
Cool until set.
Cut into squares, about 24 to 30 squares.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine, potatoes, sour cream, undiluted chicken soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and cover with 1 stick of melted margarine and corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili and whole wheat corn bread
directions: In a large, nonreactive soup kettle, warm the oil over low heat. Add the onion, carrot, garlic, red and green peppers and jalapenos.

Cover the kettle and cook the vegetables until they are very soft, about 10 minutes. Remove the lid, add the chili powder and cumin and cook an additional 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the beans and tomatoes and their juice. Increase the heat to medium and bring the chili to a simmer.
Adjust the heat to maintain a simmer and let the chili cook for 20 minutes. Stir in the salt, pepper and cilantro. Serve. Serves 4.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Mix in berries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Jell one-half of mixture in mold and then spread a layer of sour cream over jelled mixture.
Next, pour balance of gelatin mix over sour cream layer and let set until firm.

title: barbecue joes(for microwave)
directions: Put in microwave-safe bowl, cover and cook on High for 7 to 9 minutes or until bubbly and of desired consistency.

title: white christmas candy
directions: Melt candy coating over medium low heat, stirring until smooth.
Stir in peppermint candy.
Spread on waxed paper lined baking sheets; refrigerate for 8 to 10 minutes.
Break into small pieces; store in an airtight container.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, cook asparagus until tender, about 3 to 5 minutes.
If frozen, cook according to directions. Arrange asparagus and cheese in bottom of pie crust.
Beat remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour this mixture over asparagus and cheese.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook about 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: hush puppies(large recipe)
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl.
Shape into small balls and deep fry until golden brown and crusty on the outside. Makes 35 to 50 hush puppies.

title: venison roast
directions: Mix soups and sauce, pour over roast wrap in double foil and bake at 350 for 3 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Place bread cubes in large aluminum bowl.
Add chicken, onion, celery, cheese, almonds and pepper.
Toss well.
Add lemon juice and mayonnaise and mix thoroughly.
Empty into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Good luncheon specialty.
Yields 6 to 9 servings.

title: enchilada chicken soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the soups, milk, chicken, enchilada sauce and chilies; mix well. Cook until heated through. Garnish with sour cream. Yield: 7 servings.

title: strawberry angel pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Stir well.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in Cool Whip and 1 cup berries.
Spoon into crust.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Add berries on top.

title: salmon patties
directions: Saute finely chopped celery, onion and green pepper in a little butter.
Add this to remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Make small patties and fry in pan with a little oil until brown.

title: "ham made" sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide into thirds.
Roll firmly into 3 rolls.
Place on foil, shiny side next to meat.
Wrap so that seam side is up.

title: martha washington
directions: Melt margarine.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add nuts, blend well.

title: basic french bread
directions: Combine water and yeast in a mixer bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix on low speed with a dough hook until all of the flour is incorporated.
Increase to second speed and knead the dough until it is smooth and elastic.
Let the dough rise until doubled.
Punch down, divide and shape as desired.
Let rise again until doubled.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Put chicken in low casserole (about 10 x 10 x 2-inch or 9 x 12 x 2-inch) that is suitable to serve at the table.
Mix mushrooms, soup, sour cream and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, until chicken is done.
Serve with white rice or wild rice, spooning "gravy" over the rice.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients; add enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Roll to about 1/2-inch thick on floured board.
Cut out and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Serve hot.

title: no crust potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except pecans in blender for 2 or 3 minutes or until creamy.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate sprayed with Pam.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with pecans and bake another 20 minutes or until center feels firm.
If no nuts, bake for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Make in 12 individual muffin cups.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple oat pancakes
directions: In medium bowl, combine rolled oats and water; let stand 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat skillet or griddle to 375°.
Grease lightly with cooking spray.
Add remaining ingredients to rolled oats mix.
Stir well until all ingredients are moistened (will be thin).

title: italian chicken
directions: Place oil in skillet.
Pound chicken breast with side of a saucer until flat.
Beat egg in a cereal bowl and dip each chicken breast.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Brown in skillet on both sides (do not cook completely done).
Drain on paper towel.
Put 2 tablespoons Ragu in bottom of glass baking dish.
Place chicken in dish.
Pour remaining Ragu on top of chicken.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°. Makes 4 servings.

title: knock you naked cookies
directions: Combine dry cake mix, pecans and 1/3 cup evaporated milk and melted butter.
Press 1/2 batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until brown (approximately 8 minutes).
Melt caramels with 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Pour over baked lower layer.
Cover with chocolate morsels. Top with remaining batter.
Bake until brown.

title: aunt sara's crumb cake
directions: Mix until well blended and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in a large skillet.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Add pepper and carrot strips.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes (I cook a little longer).
Mix cornstarch with soy sauce; add to pan with pineapple and juice, vinegar, sugar and ginger. Bring to a full boil.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water.
Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pour pecan halves into bowl and coat well.
Bake on cookie sheet at 250° for 1 hour.
Turn every 15 minutes.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Cook sugar, chocolate and milk together.
Stir constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Then occasionally, stir to prevent burning.
Cook until small amount of mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Add butter, salt and vanilla.
Cool.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: eggnog cranberry salad
directions: In saucepan, combine pudding mix, lemon jello and 2 cups water. Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Stir in lemon juice; chill until partially set.
Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Cook and stir until dissolved.
Beat in cranberry sauce. Fold in celery and nuts.
Chill until partially set.
Prepare dessert topping according to package directions, adding nutmeg; fold into pudding mixture.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix together until you have evenly colored mix.
Add 1/4 cup mix to mug of hot water.
This makes a great gift!

title: texas caviar
directions: Soak dried peas overnight.
Drain, then cover with fresh water. Cook 35 to 49 minutes. Drain peas well. Cool.
Add peas to all other ingredients. Chill.
This will keep for weeks. Serve with Wheat Thins as a dip or as a salad.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Cut the butter in with pastry blender until crumbs form.
Press into a 10-inch pie plate. Arrange peach halves over crumb crust.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar with the cinnamon; sprinkle over peaches.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°. Beat egg yolks and sour cream; pour over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: salsa
directions: Let stand several days to meld.

title: beef stew
directions: Cover 1 1/2 lb. beef roast cut in small pieces, with water and cook until done.
About an hour. 4 medium potatoes, peeled and cut in pieces, 1 1/2 cup finely chopped celery.

Be sure and add leaves, 3 cup shredded cabbage, 1-14.5 oz can of tomatoes chopped fine, 1-14.5 oz can of green beans or peas or corn, 1-8 oz can of tomato sauce, 1 large onion chopped fine, 5 beef bouillon cubes, 1 Tbsp Mrs. Dash seasoning, 1 tsp salt, 1/2 tsp pepper about 20 minutes.
Before it is done add 1/2 cup shell macaroni or 1/4 cup rice or barley.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, and let stand for 15 minutes to dissolve sugar. Add pecan halves and fold through mixture. When well coated, remove with slotted spoon and place in a single layer on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 225° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and cool on cookie sheet. Store in a tightly covered tin.

title: cheese roll
directions: Let Velveeta cheese set out and get about room temperature. Roll Velveeta cheese out on wax paper until 1/4-inch thin.
Spread cream cheese over Velveeta cheese.
Layer chopped onions and pecans over cream cheese.
Roll into one long roll.
Chill.
Slice to eat on crackers.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook broccoli and onions in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes; drain well.
In bowl, thoroughly mix cream of chicken soup, milk, water and shredded cheese.
Stir in uncooked rice and drained broccoli.
Put into 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir once while cooking.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Place milk, butter, eggs and raisins in medium bowl.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl and toss with 2 forks for 1 minute.
Add buttermilk mixture and mix until combined.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Should sound hollow when tapped. Leave in pan 1 minute.
Then cool completely on wire rack. Contains 165 calories per 1/2-inch slice.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: You will need a gallon size jar.

title: aunt jemima maple syrup
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat.
Stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full boil, boil for 7 minutes.
Turn heat off; let cool for 15 minutes.
Add maple flavoring and stir.
When completely cool, put syrup in a covered plastic or glass container.
Makes 1 quart.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in electric mixer.
Grease and flour 8-inch pan.
Pour in mixture and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pork chops with baked beans
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper to taste.
Coat with flour and brown in oil.
Mix beans, mustard, brown sugar and ketchup in 9 x 14-inch pan and top beans with pork chops.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: peach crumb bake
directions: Layer sliced peaches in bottom of an 8-inch square baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray (Pam).
Combine graham cracker crumbs, cinnamon and nutmeg in a small bowl, stirring well.
Add margarine and stir until well combined.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumb mixture over peaches and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serving amount is 1/2 cup at 78 calories.
Diabetic Exchange:
1 fruit and 1/2 fat.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken breasts; cut into small pieces.
Mix soups, yogurt, onions, water chestnuts and chicken.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Crush cornflakes and put on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue pecans
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add the pecan halves and toss to coat.
Bake the nuts on a cookie sheet for about 25 minutes in a preheated 325° oven, stirring often.
Let cool before serving.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Toss blueberries with 2 tablespoons flour and set aside.
Sift remaining dry ingredients, except nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating portions with cream, beginning and ending with cream. Fold in floured berries.
Pour batter in lightly greased pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inches.
Sprinkle with mixture of remaining sugar and nutmeg.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican coffee
directions: Place coffee in coffee filter or filter basket; add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add water to coffeemaker and brew.
Combine brown sugar, chocolate syrup and milk in a large heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until brown sugar dissolves. Stir in coffee and vanilla.
Serve immediately with a dollop of whipped cream; garnish, if desired.
Yield:
6 1/2 cups.

title: brownie pie(sugar-free)
directions: Beat eggs until light and thickened.
Add oleo, sorbitol and sugar replacement.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and salt; set aside.
Add baking chocolate.
Alternately add flour and milk to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until pie tests done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Beat together Crisco, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs, beating until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture and rolled oats. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: overnight tossed salad
directions: Place half the lettuce in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, sugar and pepper.
Top with layer of eggs, the peas, bacon, remaining lettuce, green onion, celery and cheese.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over the top to cover.
Place tight cover on bowl and refrigerate 24 hours.
Toss just before serving.
Makes 8 servings as a main dish; 12 as a side dish in a meal.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Whip milk, eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla together with egg beater.
Stir in enough snow to get ice cream consistency.
Serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat sweetened milk and peanut butter.
Add Bisquick and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart, flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: dutch slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pepper, onion and carrots.
Pour sugar over all; set aside.
Combine all remaining ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Pour over cabbage and stir. Refrigerate.

title: red-eye stew
directions: Put cooking oil in skillet and get hot.
Salt and pepper meat; sear good.
Add onion and garlic; sear (mince onion).
Add the tomato sauce and chili powder.
Add water to about 1-inch from top. Put lid on and cook about 2 hours on medium heat, then add the potatoes which have been cut up in small pieces.
Put lid back on and cook about 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Sift together the first 7 ingredients.
Add the eggs, oil and vanilla. Mix well and add the pears. Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes (or a little longer).
Nuts may be added.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll dough out on a well-greased pizza pan. Bake as directed. Mix equal parts cream cheese and sugar and spread on cookie dough. Slice fresh fruit:
kiwi, blueberries, peaches, strawberries, grapes, bananas, etc.

title: monkey bread
directions: Boil 1 cup sugar, 3/4 cup butter and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon. Cut the biscuits into fourths.
Combine the rest of the sugar and cinnamon into a bowl with a lid.
Place a few of the biscuit fourths into the bowl and seal it.
Shake it until the biscuits are completely covered.
Place them into a pan (ideally an 8 x 8-inch pan or close to it).
Continue to do this in layers in the pan.
When finished, pour the mixture over the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until biscuits look done.
After cooked, it tastes really good with butter on it!!!!

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix half of butter with spinach and cream cheese.
Place in casserole and top with stuffing mix.
Drizzle with remaining butter.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine shortening and onion in skillet.
Brown.
Add mustard and ground beef.
Brown.
Add tomato catsup and pork and beans, mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375° or until brown.

title: nut sticks
directions: Cook butter and sugar on low heat until sugar is dissolved. Cool.
When cool, add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Mix thoroughly. Add flour and baking powder; then add the nuts.
Place in a well buttered 16 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Leave in pan to cool, then cut.

title: desperation quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line the pie shell with half the cheese slices.
Mix together the carrots and celery.
Spread half of the vegetable mixture evenly in the cheese-lined pie shell.
Then add nuts or tuna.
Try to distribute as evenly as possible.
Add the remaining vegetables.
Beat eggs, milk and soy sauce.
Pour on top of vegetable layer.
Top with remaining cheese.
At this point, pie can be baked or refrigerated for future use.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave undisturbed for another 15 minutes (this finishes the baking and gives the cheese a chance to set up.
Make sure to put something under the pie pan, because it sometimes bubbles over.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13 pan. Spread coconut and pecans in bottom of the pan. Mix cake mix as directed on box, then pour over coconut and pecans. Stir together margarine, confectioners sugar and softened cream cheese. Spread evenly over cake. Seal to sides of pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: m & m casserole
directions: Carefully rip one corner from the M&M's bag. Pour into the casserole dish. Do not pour from more than one foot above the dish as the M&M's will bounce out. Replace lid. This dish is a hit at all get togethers. There are never any leftovers. For variation, try plain M&M's.

title: tangy norwegian flounder casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine or oil until limp. Stir in flour and remove pan from heat. Add milk and return to heat.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Add salt, dill weed, lemon juice, pepper and mustard.
Place mixture in casserole.
Place fish on bottom. Cover with potatoes.
Cover with bread crumbs and margarine cut up on top. Sprinkle paprika.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Serves 2.
Double ingredients for 4.

title: kristy's microwave snack
directions: First get half of Velveeta and then get can of Ro-Tel and cream of mushroom soup.
Cut the Velveeta up and mix all of the ingredients together.
Microwave for 4 minutes.

title: kentucky bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and 1 egg until crumbly. Put in 9 x 13 pan sprayed with Pam.
Whip sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs until creamy.
Pour over top of crust.
Bake at 325 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: good coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in sheet pan according to directions on box.. While hot, poke holes in cake and pour in pina colada and Eagle Brand milk. Let cool, then spread Cool Whip over cake. Spread one package frozen coconut over cake and refrigerate.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix water, oats and margarine in large mixing bowl.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add sugars, eggs, flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Put chunks in first.
Add pineapple juice and orange juice; stir well.
Add vodka or champagne.
Top with sherbet.

title: hillbilly cookies (no bake)
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 4 minutes (longer if double batch).
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until blended and drop on wax paper.

title: salmon patties
directions: Flake salmon; add all other ingredients and form into patties. May be pan-fried or broiled.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Add Ro-Tel, picante sauce and 1/2 can of chopped green chilies.
Mix ingredients and cover dish. Microwave for 8 to 12 minutes.
Serve with tostada chips.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook water and raisins in microwave until puffed up.
Mix in order.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix pineapple, juice, flour, sugar and cheese together.
Put in baking dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers and spread over top of mixture.
Pour melted margarine on top of crackers.
Bake at 350 for 25-30 minutes.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions and cool. Add green onions, bell pepper, olives and water chestnuts to rice. Separately, mix chicken broth or milk to mayonnaise. Add curry powder and stir. Pour into rice and mix well.

title: marinated hot dogs
directions: Mix together and marinate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked brie
directions: Cut off rind of Brie.
Place in a small souffle dish, approximately the same size as cheese.
Combine butter and brown sugar; spread on top of cheese.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.
Serve with thinly sliced French bread.
Serves 4.
(Brown sugar may be omitted.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter, in baking dish, then slice butter in pieces and put on top of casserole for the top to brown. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute bacon, celery and onion.
Add potatoes; continue to saute for several minutes.
Add enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil; cook for 5 minutes.
Add cream-style corn and evaporated milk.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, until potatoes are tender.

title: scented cinnamon ornaments
directions: In medium bowl, combine cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Add applesauce and glue.
Stir to combine.
Work mixture with hands 2 to 3 minutes or until dough is smooth and ingredients are thoroughly mixed.
Divide into 4 portions.
Roll out each dough portion to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut dough with cookie cutters of desired shapes.
Using straw or toothpick, make a small hole in top of ornament.
Place cutouts on wire rack and allow to dry at room temperature for several days.
Turn over ornaments once each day.
Thread ribbon through hole in ornament.
Do not eat.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Spray jello ring or Bundt pan with Pam.
Punch holes in cake with ice pick or kitchen fork.
Dissolve jello with boiling water in small bowl.
Add 1/2 thawed strawberries.
Pour into jello ring (or Bundt pan).
Push whole cake down in ring over liquid and strawberries.
Put in freezer for 30 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream and remaining strawberries.

title: potatoes deluxe(serves 12)
directions: Thaw hash brown potatoes for 1/2 hour.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix all the ingredients in bowl.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: roasted rice
directions: Spread the rice in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes until the rice is golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Put the rice in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in the boiling water and add it to the rice.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Blend; cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large pan and simmer for 20 minutes.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add beef to pinto bean mixture.
Simmer for an additional 15 minutes.
Pour into large dish.
Mix cornbread according to package directions and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° until cornbread is brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash, cap and drain strawberries.
Set aside until drained good.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add water and cook on top of stove until thick and glossy.
Stir constantly.
Place strawberries in pie crust.
Pour mixture over berries and put in refrigerator until ready to slice.
Put whipped cream on top.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into a large bowl.
Make a well in the center and add in order sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla; beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Stir in carrots, coconut, walnuts and pineapple until well blended. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Spread with cream cheese frosting.
Store in refrigerator.

title: methodist cookies
directions: Mix oleo and sugar well.
Add egg yolks.
Add flour (small amount at a time), then vanilla.
This batter will be thick. Spread smoothly in pan.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Blend pumpkin with beaten egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, gelatin, milk, salt and spices in a heavy saucepan.
Cook and stir over moderate heat until thickened; cool.
Beat egg whites until frothy; add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, a tablespoon at a time, and continue beating until stiff, but not dry.
Fold egg whites into cooled pumpkin mixture and pour into prepared pie shell.
Cool thoroughly.

title: killer beans
directions: Drain
kidney beans.
Mix with all other ingredients in a 12-inch Dutch oven and cook covered for 30 minutes.

title: cafe mocha mix
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: cream cheese braid
directions: Heat sour cream over low heat.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water in large mixing bowl, stirring until yeast dissolves.
Add sour cream mixture, eggs and flour.
Mix well; cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Roll each onto well floured board into 12 x 8-inch rectangles.
Spread 1/4 cream cheese mixture onto each rectangle.
Roll up in jelly roll fashion, starting with long side.
Pinch edges together, folding ends under slightly.
Place roll seam side down on lightly greased baking sheet.
Slit each roll at 2-inch intervals 2/3 way through dough to resemble braid.
Cover; let rise for 1 hour until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Spread with glaze while bread is still hot.
May then freeze or refrigerate.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill before serving.

title: white clam sauce
directions: In a medium sized skillet, saute garlic in very little oil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add clams and sherry and saute over high heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add butter and saute all together for 1 minute. Serve over linguine cooked al dente.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
In a saucepan over low heat, melt chips with margarine.
In a large mixer bowl, beat chocolate mixture with remaining ingredients except nuts until smooth.
Add nuts. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Good with ice cream!

title: black joe
directions: Mix all ingredients well; batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured pan and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread evenly on tortillas. Roll tortillas up.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Cut into 1-inch slices and serve.

title: shrimp and cauliflower in dill mayonnaise
directions: In large pot of boiling water with 1 tablespoon lemon juice, cook cauliflower for 7 to 10 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Cool under cold water; drain thoroughly.
Combine cauliflower, celery and shrimp.
Mix together mayonnaise, remaining 1 tablespoon lemon juice and dill.
Add to cauliflower mixture; toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: our favorite devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add melted chocolate.
Beat egg yolks; add water and extract and blend.
Gradually add yolk mixture to chocolate mixture; beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add alternately with milk, blending well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; fold into batter.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 to 35 minutes, or until cake springs back when touched lightly.

title: quick orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, cottage cheese, Cool Whip and orange slices gently with spoon.
Put on lettuce leaves.
Chill.

title: quick lunchbox cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chocolate chips and nuts (if used).
Pour batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except garlic together; about an hour before using, add garlic.
Makes 6 pints.
Can be frozen.

title: chocolate mocha pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla. Add beaten egg yolks.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquids.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into paper cups placed in muffin tins.
Freeze.
Makes 8 to 9 servings.

title: brown bread
directions: Put All-Bran in milk to soak.
In another bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Add molasses, egg, flour, soda, salt and milk. Add bran mixture.
Add 1/2 cup of raisins and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pecan sticky buns
directions: Heat brown sugar, corn syrup and 3 tablespoons butter in pan until sugar dissolves.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Arrange pecans evenly.
In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, undissolved yeast and salt.
Stir water, milk and 1/3 cup butter into dry ingredients.
Stir in eggs and remaining flour. Knead 8 minutes.
Roll to rectangle.
Melt remaining butter; brush on dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up as a jelly roll, pinch seam and cut into 8 pieces.
Place in pan.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Remove from refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Invert onto serving tray.

title: low calorie bread pudding
directions: Soak bread cubes in scalded milk for 5 minutes; add Sweet 'N Low, cinnamon and raisins.
Pour over beaten eggs; add vanilla and blend well. Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in slow oven at 325°
about 50 minutes until firm.
Makes 4 servings.
One serving has 114 calories.

title: shish kebabs
directions: Marinate the meat in a mixture of 1 bottle French dressing and 1/2 bottle Russian or any barbecue sauce the night before.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Combine all your fruit in a large bowl.
Add the cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Blend in the powdered Jell-O until completely mixed together.
Chill for a few hours.

title: old fashion country gravy
directions: Make in heavy skillet.
When drippings (grease) are hot, add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until brown (not burned).
Add milk; boil until thick.
If too thick, add more milk.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to a simmer.
Add salt.
Peel potatoes and cut into pieces.
Add to broth.
Then add onions, parsley and whipping cream.
Simmer five more minutes.
Add butter.
Crumble bacon on top.
Stir and serve hot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat more.
Beat all ingredients.
Put in greased loaf pans 3/4 full.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: biscuit hamburger pizzas
directions: Butter 3 cookie sheets.
Flatten 6 biscuits per sheet to 4 to 5-inch circles.
Spoon on 2 tablespoons of tomato sauce on each biscuit.
Brown hamburger in skillet and spoon hamburger, 1 to 2 ounces, on each biscuit.
Spread remaining ingredients as toppings as you would on regular pizza.
Other toppings can be added or deleted according to your tastes.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove and serve.

title: microwave chicken
directions: Put chicken in glass dish.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake on High in microwave for 9 minutes. Turn over; bake 9 minutes or until done.

title: oriental noodle and pasta salad
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil.
Blanch carrots until crisp-tender, remove from pot with slotted spoon.
Cook pasta in same water to desired doneness, drain and rinse with cold water. In a large bowl, combine pasta, sugar snap peas, carrots and onion.
In a small bowl, combine oil, sugar and contents of Oriental flavor packet, blending well. Pour over pasta mixture; toss to coat.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour to blend flavors. Just before serving, break the uncooked instant noodles into pieces and cashews in half.
Toss sesame seed with chilled salad. Scatter noodle and cashew pieces over top of salad.
Serves ten.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Stir ketchup, mustard and Miracle Whip.
Mix into ground beef with salt and pepper.
Add onions and green peppers.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin supper
directions: Slice top off pumpkin and scoop out seeds.
(May be toasted later.)
The size of the pumpkin can be adjusted to your oven height by slicing the bottom half down and readjusting lid.
With a melon baller, remove meat without breaking shell.
You'll need a strong arm.
Set aside in a 10-inch pie plate or casserole to fit. Saute lamb cubes or meatballs in the oil until browned.
Remove. In the same oil cook onion, garlic and pumpkin balls.
Stir until onions are translucent.
Add flour and spices and cook 5 minutes more.
Add remaining ingredients and meat.
Season with salt and pepper.
If using lamb cubes, simmer 1 hour, uncovered.
Reduce time to 20 minutes if using meatballs, or until sauce thickens somewhat.
Pour mixture into shell; top with lid.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until pumpkin is golden.
This is certain to be a surprising and entertaining meal as well as a delicious one.
May be served with herb bread and hot mulled cider.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon fluff dessert - diabetic
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in medium bowl 2 minutes, or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 3 hours, or until firm.
Cut gelatin into small cubes.
Stir pudding mix and pineapple in small bowl until well blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Stir in gelatin cubes.
Refrigerate 1 hour, or until ready to serve. Yields 8 servings.

title: chili
directions: Chop onion and cook until clear. Add chuck and brown. Add chili powder, salt, Worcestershire sauce and tomatoes.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased 10-inch iron skillet for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: quick and easy banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In large mixing bowl, cream together eggs, Crisco, sugar, vanilla and then add milk and flour.
Mix with spoon, then use hand mixer on medium for 1 minute.
Pour into 2 well-greased cake pans and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown, then cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, cook broccoli by directions on package, then drain.
In a large skillet, saute 1/2 cup oleo, onions and mushrooms.
Cook until tender.
Add soup, flour and cheese.
Stir well.
Combine mixture with broccoli and mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. In a small saucepan, melt remaining 1/2 cup margarine.
Add cracker crumbs and mix well.
Top casserole with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: harvey house slaw
directions: Mix together the vegetables and sprinkle the sugar on top. Set aside.

title: mint tea syrup
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes to make a syrup.
Add tea bag, mint and lemon juice.
Let stand 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Put 1-inch of syrup in glass and fill with water and ice.

title: nut loaf
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and nuts.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt, alternately with milk 3 times.
Add vanilla.
Pour combined mixture into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder, sugar and soda.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Cut in shortening; mix only until blended.
Let rise 1 hour or until doubled.
Roll out onto a floured surface, knead lightly a few times.
Roll out dough and cut into biscuit size. May be stored several days in covered container in refrigerator. Will keep well.
Bake at 375° or 400° until brown.

title: caramel candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and salt.
Boil until it spins a thread (232°).
Reduce heat a little.
Add butter and milk in small portions, alternating, beginning and ending with butter.
Cook until it reaches 245°.
Stir all the time with a wooden spoon. Takes about an hour.
Pour into buttered 9 X 13 dish to cool (overnight is better).
Cut into cubes and wrap in wax paper. Note:
DO NOT make when raining or damp.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crumble graham crackers and mix in oleo; press into pan.
Beat until smooth the cream cheese, eggs and 1 1/4 cups sugar, then pour over cracker mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: balloon wine
directions: Mix juice and sugar with enough warm water (not hot) to nearly fill the jug. Dissolve the yeast in a small amount of warm water and add to jug. Mix thoroughly. Put the neck of the clean deflated balloon securely over the top of the jug. Allow to stand at room temperature until working has stopped (about 2 weeks). Do not remove or disturb the balloon, by the end of 2 weeks it will begin to deflate. The wine can be put in a cooler for a couple of weeks to serve.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix altogether.
Let set in refrigerator 2 to 4 hours.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: gnocchi(potato pasta)
directions: Boil the potatoes until soft.
Remove skins; mash.
When cool, empty onto a floured board or counter.
Break the egg and sprinkle the flour over the mixture, then knead until a smooth dough is attained.
Prepare a pot of salted, boiling water.
Roll the dough into long "ropes" about the diameter of a pencil.
Cut off dough in 1/2-inch pieces and boil until pasta rises to the top; drain. Serve with tomato sauce or sauteed vegetables.

title: chicken ala suisse
directions: Place one can of soup on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place the chicken breasts (halved) on top of the soup.
Place the cheese on the chicken.
Cover this with the other can of soup. Sprinkle the stuffing over all.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue cooking for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water and drain.
Cook beans in water and salt until tender.
Place in baking pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 4 hours at 300°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet.
Drain.
Stir in pizza sauce.
In casserole dish, arrange noodles on bottom until dish bottom is covered.
Top with hamburger mixture.
Top with pepperoni.
Add cheese on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cheese starts turning brown.

title: egg salad melt
directions: Mix together, chopped up hard boiled eggs, mayonnaise and celery. Season. Lightly toast the bread. Place 3 slices of the bread on a cookie sheet. Top each with 1/3 of the egg salad. Top with the cheese. Place under a hot broiler until the cheese has just melted. Top with the remaining toasted bread. Serve immediately.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into balls.
Bake for 30 minutes; first 15 minutes, bake at 350°, then reduce heat to 325° for 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking pan or dish.
Place cheese on top.
Spoon wine or water over top.
Evenly sprinkle dressing on top and drizzle butter over top.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into small cubes.
Brown in shortening about 5 minutes or until tender.
Add soy sauce and water; simmer about 10 minutes.
Add onion; simmer 5 minutes.
Add peppers; cook until tender.
Thicken with cornstarch and serve over steamed rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in fat with a fork until crumbly.
Add milk and mix enough to wet the dry ingredients.
Drop dough from a tablespoon onto greased baking pan.
Bake at 450° (very hot oven) for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 12 or 6 biscuits.

title: blueberry trifle
directions: Cream softened cream cheese, condensed milk, powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Remove brown crust from cake and break cake into pieces.
Layer:
1/2 of the cake, 1/2 of the cream cheese mixture and 1/2 of the pie filling.
Repeat.
Top with cool whip. Refrigerate until set or overnight.

title: quick pizza dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese with Italian seasoning with electric mixer until well blended.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate. Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, the pizza sauce and another 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Top with the green and red peppers.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until thoroughly heated through and cheese is melted.
Serve with bread sticks.

title: bacon crisps
directions: Break crackers along perforation.
Wrap 1/2 piece bacon around a cracker.
May need to secure with toothpicks.
Place on cookie sheet; sprinkle heavily with paprika.
Bake in a preheated 200° oven until bacon is done, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let set a few minutes so that bacon can crisp.
Serve warm.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: In a small saucepan, combine and boil 1 minute the eggs, flour, sugar and juices from oranges and pineapple.
Add orange gelatin and chill.

title: grandma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet and pat down with fork.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: bulldog brittle
directions: Melt oleo and butter in boiler.
Add sugar.
Bring to boil. Stir constantly.
Boil exactly 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand until cool. Break into pieces.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Dough will be thick.
Spread into greased 10 x 5 x 1-inch pan. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes; cool before cutting.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan, mixing well. Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Chill 2 or 3 hours. Place peaches in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in 1/3 cup of sugar.
Place in blender and blend until smooth; set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and let cool.
Combine coffee creamer and 1/4 cup of sugar in a large bowl; stir well.
Gradually stir in egg mixture.
Add pureed peaches, gelatin mixture and sour cream; beat with a wire whisk until smooth.
Pour into freezer can of 1 gallon freezer. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Let ripen 2 hours before serving.

title: lo-cal spinach dip
directions: Serve with crackers or other vegetables.

title: ranch stew
directions: Brown the ground beef, onion and bell pepper. Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat or slow cooker for about 2 hours.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: In top of double boiler, place warm water and egg yolks; beat until creamy (3 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add lemon, salt and pepper.
Beat in butter a little at a time until smooth.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients and fry them in a frying pan.

title: creamy turkey casserole
directions: Cook celery in margarine until tender.
Stir in turkey gravy mix right from the envelope and water.
Heat just to boiling. Blend in diced turkey and sour cream.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cucumber-radish salad
directions: Stir together first five ingredients.
Add vegetables; toss to coat.
Makes about 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: jamaican oxtail
directions: Season the oxtail with salt and pepper.
Fry until brown. Place in pressure cooker.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add with thyme to the oxtail.
Add flour to the remaining oil and stir well with a spoon.
Cook this roux for about 8 minutes until it is rich brown in color.
Add water and stir well.
When the liquid boils pour it over the ingredients in the pressure cooker.
Pressure cook for 40 minutes.
Cook, without pressure, for 20 minutes more.
Stir in ketchup, lime juice and beans.
Serve hot with white rice and vegetables.
Serves 6.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup crumbs and almonds. Mix well.
Top with crumbs and almonds.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 servings.

title: easy waffles
directions: Mix ingredients (do not overmix).
Batter should be a little rough.
Pour about 2/3 cup of mixture on a waffle maker.

title: kentucky butter cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cream 1 cup butter and 2 cups sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time. Mix buttermilk and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Starting and ending with the dry ingredients, stir flour and milk into the creamed mixture. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 50 to 60 minutes at 325°. While warm, prick with fork.
Heat, but do not boil the last 1/2 cup butter, 1 cup sugar, water and vanilla.
Drizzle over warm cake.

title: brandied sweet potatoes
directions: In shallow pan or baking dish, arrange sliced cooked potatoes. Mix all dry ingredients.
Stir in water.
Cook over low heat until clear, then add lemon juice and brandy.
Pour over sweet potatoes and bake about 30 minutes at 375° until glazed.
Baste occasionally.
Yields about 8 servings.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, pepper and salt.
Set aside.
Cut each chicken breast in half; dip in melted butter. Roll in crumb mixture.

title: puffy cheese slices
directions: Set oven control to broil at 550°.
Broil bread 5-inches from heat until golden brown on 1 side.
Turn.
Blend cheese, egg, mustard and salt. Spread over untoasted side of bread.
Broil until cheese bubbles. Makes
5 open-faced sandwiches.

title: broccoli cheese potatoes
directions: Place sliced potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle, salt, pepper and garlic.
Mix soup and 3/4 can of milk.
Pour over potatoes and dab butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add onion and taco seasoning; saute.
In a big soup pot, put all canned ingredients including all juice. Add meat and onion. Stir and simmer for 1 hour.
If it is too thick for your taste, add some beef bouillon to "loosen" it up. Freezes well.

title: pasta primavera with shrimp(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook fettucine in salted water to desired doneness as directed on package.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Meanwhile, in skillet, melt 3 tablespoons margarine.
Saute onion and garlic until tender.
Add shrimp and saute 2 to 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Remove shrimp from skillet.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Thaw berries.
Mix undrained berries, eggs, and oil.
Sift dry ingredients into strawberry mixture, reserving about 1/2 cup flour to sprinkle over nuts.
Blend thoroughly.
Add flour to nuts, coating well.
Add to batter then pour into well greased and floured 9 x 5 loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger in a large deep frying pan, drain grease and salt to taste.
Drain soup, add it and spaghetti to hamburger. Heat long enough to heat soup and spaghetti through.
Serve immediately.

title: sweet cornbread casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
(Check with toothpick at center to see if done.)
Remove and add cheese over top.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Steam zucchini until tender and place in greased casserole dish.
Layer all the cheese.
