Next, layer with soup mixture. Next, melt margarine and add to packs of stuffing mix.
Place on top and bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and Crisco oil.
Mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt and combine with first mixture.
Mix vanilla, zucchini and pecans with the rest. Put in well-greased and floured loaf pans (2).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes (45 minutes if in 6 small pans).

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 12 muffins or 1 cake.
Bake at 500°.
Don't overbake.
Take out when looks brown.

title: homemade buns
directions: Heat milk, Crisco, sugar and salt.
Let cool to lukewarm. Beat eggs, water, yeast and flour.
Add to first mixture, using electric mixer until you can't beat anymore.
Then knead with hands.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt together margarine and semi-sweet chocolate pieces.
Add sugar, eggs, coconut and pecans.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzel sticks, 3/4 cup melted margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pat in a 13 x 10-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for minutes.
Cool.

title: crispy yam casserole
directions: Mix yams and milk; pat into greased pan.
Dot yams with butter.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over yams.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 25 servings.

title: shrimp in garlic butter(microwave; easy)
directions: Place butter in microwave-safe dish (8 or 9-inch); a Corning Ware dish works great.
Heat butter 35 to 45 seconds to melt. Stir in garlic powder and parsley flakes.
Place shrimp in colander; run cold water over to clean and separate.
Drain.
Stir shrimp into butter mixture to evenly coat.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes on High.
Stir every 2 minutes.
When shrimp are tender and opaque, let stand 1 1/2 minutes before serving.
Serve with toothpicks.
Fresh shrimp may be used if deveined and peeled.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 cups.

title: 1-2-3 spaghetti
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet on medium-high heat; drain.
Add spaghetti and soup; toss lightly.
Microwave process cheese spread as directed on label.
Stir into spaghetti mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt together.
In separate bowl, mix Wesson oil, eggs and sugar together.
Add flour mixture to sugar mix.
Add carrots.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in 2 layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk according to package directions.
Add container of Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas and cream. Refrigerate.

title: gazpacho
directions: Into a large bowl, chop the vegetables and herbs.
Add the remaining ingredients as listed.
Blend all in a blender by batches.
Chill.

title: dumplings
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients well.
Add eggs and milk.
Put on floured board and knead gently until firm.
Roll very thin and let stand 30 minutes.
Put into
chicken or squirrel broth, boiling vigorously.
Cook until done or about 30 minutes.

title: apple streudel
directions: Cut margarine in pieces over apples.
Sprinkle with sugar, flour and cinnamon mixture.
Put on top crust.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes more. Mix powdered sugar and milk to make a paste.
Spread over streudel while hot.

title: pop's spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium-sized saucepan.
Stir slowly over low heat for 2 minutes.
Cover pan; continue to cook over low heat (stir as necessary) for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: veal in wine with mushrooms
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add veal and saute until browned.
Remove veal to oven casserole.
Saute onions lightly in skillet.
Add undiluted mushroom soup, oregano, wine and juice from mushrooms (if available).
Simmer gently for a few minutes.
Add to casserole. Add mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 325° to 350° for about 2 1/2 hours, stirring once or twice.
Can be frozen.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
Serve over wild rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In bowl, mix ground beef, chili, tomato sauce and 1/2 can enchilada sauce.
In casserole, layer 1/3 beef mixture, 6 slices cheese and arrange 6 tortilla halves; repeat layers.
Spread remaining bean mixture on 2nd layer of tortillas.
Top with cheese, rest of enchilada sauce and onions.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes, until cheese begins to bubble.

title: celia's cole slaw
directions: Add all ingredients together; mix well.
May need to add more of onion, garlic powder to your own taste.

title: granola bars
directions: Stir well and press into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.

title: my favorite pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Let rise 15 minutes.
Spread out on cookie sheet or pizza pan.
I like to prebake mine until lightly browned, then add my toppings.

title: blueberry sour cream pie
directions: Combine sour cream, flour, 3 tablespoons brown sugar and egg. Beat well.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture into crust.
Combine blueberries and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread over mixture in crust.
Top with remaining cream mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken and almond stir-fry(makes 2 servings)
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1 1/2 x 3/4-inch strips.
Combine egg white, cornstarch, salt and sugar; pour over chicken.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Blanch slivered almonds by submersion in boiling water for two minutes.
Fry almonds in 1 tablespoon peanut oil until golden brown.
Do not burn or over fry!
Remove from wok and drain.
Stir-fry chicken in 3 tablespoons oil until chicken turns white.
Stir-fry pea pods in 1 tablespoon oil until crisp.
Remove and drain.
Stir-fry garlic (crushed) and ginger slices in 1 tablespoon oil for 1 minute.
Remove ginger and garlic from oil and discard ginger and garlic.
To the flavored oil, add chicken, sherry, soy sauce, pea pods and almonds.
Heat in covered wok over low heat until hot.
Serve over rice and enjoy.
Makes 2 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
If pork is used, cut it in small pieces and fry until lightly browned before adding to the other ingredients.
Mold mixture into a loaf.
Place on tough paper or foil on rack in uncovered pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, and pour into pie shells.
Put on top crust, and bake at 350° until brown.
Serve hot with a salad.
Very good.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Sift all ingredients together.
Place in airtight container.

title: white bean soup
directions: Saute onions, carrots, celery and garlic in butter.
Add water, thyme, pepper and gravy mix and bring to a boil.
Add sausage and beans; reduce heat, cover and simmer about 15 minutes.

title: teresa's poor man's jelly
directions: Puree tomatoes in food processor or blender.
Place in saucepan with sugar and lemon juice.
Bring to boil, simmer 25 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add jello, any flavor, stir until dissolved.
Freeze.

title: dump cake
directions: In an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, spread the crushed pineapple, spoon the cherry pie filling (any fruit pie filling is good), then sprinkle cake mix over this.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Pour melted oleo evenly over this.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: black bean gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours.

title: banana-sour cream jubilee
directions: Combine all ingredients in order and mix.
Pour into paper baking cups and freeze.
Serve on lettuce.
Garnish with additional marschino cherries, nuts, lemon twists, mint leaves or orange slices.
Serves 12.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower
directions: Cut cauliflower flowerets from main stem and steam until tender.
Place in mixing bowl and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in small bowl and toss with cauliflower.
Serve hot.

title: aunt bobby's baked beans
directions: Use large or #2 1/2 cans of beans.
Combine all ingredients and bake 350-375° for at least one hour or until mixture starts to thicken.

title: tamale squares
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water, pineapple, salt and grated carrots (and celery).
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or a gelatin mold.
Cut in squares or slices and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut them in half and scoop out the meat.
The more meat you scoop out, the crispier the skins will be.
(The meat can be used for mashed potatoes.)
Cook bacon until crisp and crumble.
Mix all cheeses together.
Heat oil and drop in skins, turning occasionally.
When skins are light brown, remove and drain on a paper towel.
Place skins on a baking sheet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fill with cheeses and bacon.
Broil until cheeses melt.
Serve with Ranch dressing, sour cream or your favorite dip.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well and add last 2 ingredients.
Press dough into a 15 x 10-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Glaze while hot.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and fill churn up with milk.
Add 2 more cups of sugar if peaches are unsweetened.

title: marinated kabobs
directions: Cut meat and vegetables in 1-inch squares.

title: heavenly orange fluff
directions: Mix gelatin with hot water. Stir in undiluted orange juice. Cool. Add oranges and pineapple to gelatin mixture.
Pour into an 11 x 13-inch dish and congeal.

title: dot's coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake in layers at 350° until done.

title: beets and pineapple
directions: Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Stir in pineapple (with syrup).
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add lemon juice, oleo and beets.
Cook over medium heat until heated thoroughly.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook Minute rice as directed.
Mix all together; put in 2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Blend eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture alternately with milk, extracts and coconut.
Pour into pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pan while making sauce.

title: kaylene's potato soup
directions: Saute the onion in margarine until tender.
Add the chopped potatoes.
Pour enough water just to cover.
Cook on medium heat until potatoes are soft.

title: low-fat shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove shells from shrimp, leaving shell on tail section only.
Devein, wash under running water and drain on paper towels.
Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with a nonfat cooking spray.
Blend together liquid Butter Buds, lite salt, garlic and 2 tablespoons parsley.
Pour into prepared dish. Arrange shrimp in single layer in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp.
Sprinkle with lemon peel, lemon juice and remaining parsley.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer, or until just tender.
Arrange shrimp over cooked rice.
Pour garlic-Butter Buds mixture over shrimp.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Do not overcook the shrimp or they will be tough.
If using smaller shrimp, cut down on cooking time.
Serve with sourdough or French bread to soak up the sauce.
Yields 8 servings.

title: black raspberry jello dessert salad
directions: In 1 bowl, mix raspberry jello and hot water.
In another bowl mix cream cheese and sugar; cream together.
In another bowl, put graham crackers, melted butter and a little sugar.
In another bowl, beat milk until stiff peaks form.
Mix jello and cream cheese mixtures.
Fold in pineapple and nuts, then fold in whipped milk. Put most of graham cracker mix on bottom of pan.
Top with filling. Sprinkle rest of graham cracker crumbs on top.
Chill.

title: brilliant raspberry dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl; beat until smooth and well mixed.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve with apples, bananas, pears, kiwi, carrots or pretzels.

title: all american
directions: Cook and stir meat and onion, in a large skillet, until browned.
Drain fat.
Stir in corn (with liquid) and remaining ingredients.
Heat mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until noodles are tender, about 30 minutes.

title: sour pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and quarter lengthwise.
Pack in 3-quart jars. Mix ingredients and bring to the boiling point.
Pour over cucumbers.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown meat; add onions.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Cook on low heat until hot.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter, butter and powdered sugar.
Roll into balls.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine eggs, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Blend in sour cream.
Pour into crusts.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Chill 5 hours.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into prepared crust. Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with strawberries and desired amount of glaze.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease muffin tins generously, then heat very hot before pouring in batter.
Sift flour before measuring.

title: popcorn peanut butter squares
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar and peanut butter in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil while stirring constantly.
Over low heat, boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from the heat and add popcorn. Toss with wooden spoons (mixture will be hot) to coat well and press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 18 good sized squares.

title: cherry (red) punch
directions: Combine
ingredients
and add water to make one gallon. When ready to serve, add 1 large ginger ale.

title: cream cheese tea bars
directions: Line 1 (9 x 13-inch) sheet cake pan with 1 can crescent roll dough.
Mix on low speed cream cheese and powdered sugar to a spreading consistency.
Spread mixture over dough evenly.
Top with 2nd can crescent roll dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add flour and chili powder.
Make a paste. Add tomato juice.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Grate cheese; add onion. Soften corn tortillas in sauce.
Fill with cheese and fold in half. Arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour remaining sauce on top.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 18 enchiladas.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. Cut in shortening until size of small peas.
Add milk and grapefruit juice all at once.
Mix quickly.
This mixture will be quite moist.
Knead on well-floured board a few times.
Roll and cut out biscuits.

title: green noodle and ham casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon margarine until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings, gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickens.
Add cheese, ham and mushrooms; stir until cheese is melted.
In 10 x 6-inch baking dish, layer half of noodles and sauce, repeat layers.
Top with crumbs tossed with 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients except 1 cup pecans.
Cream. Chill overnight.
Next day, shape into ball.
Roll in 1 cup chopped pecans or parsley.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the shortening, egg and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (10 minutes on bottom rack and 10 on top).

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in 400° oven until soft, 40 to 60 minutes.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop potato pulp from shell.
Combine other ingredients.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Pile lightly into potato shells.
Top with grated cheese and bacon bits.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven until lightly browned.

title: chicken rice delight
directions: Combine cooked rice, pimentos and cooked chicken.
Fold warm gravy into mixture until mixture is coated.
Serve warm or chill.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together in large pitcher and serve over ice.

title: divinity
directions: Boil together the sugar, syrup, salt and water to 260 degrees; soft crack stage on candy thermometer. Add to egg whites keeping syrup hot. Add vanilla and Jello. Beat until it holds a soft peak and begins to lose its gloss. Working quickly, drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: piazza
directions: Place dough on pizza pan.
Saute onion and garlic.
Mix with drained broccoli, salt and pepper.
Mix bag of cheese and 2 eggs. Add broccoli mix to dough.
Pour cheese mixture on top.
Dribble oil around edge of dough.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pie mix delight
directions: Combine Eagle Brand condensed milk, lemon juice, cherry pie filling
and pineapple;
mix.
Fold in whipped topping and nuts. Pour into pan or fluted cups.
Cover and freeze.

title: summer rollups
directions: Chop the onion and peppers. Put in everything else. Roll up in tortilla like burritos with both sides open. Refrigerate 2 hours. Cut each tortilla into 8 pieces.

title: roast chicken italiana
directions: Sprinkle outside and cavity of chicken with salt, pepper and onion powder.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
In blender, combine parsley, basil leaves, poultry seasoning, salt, pepper, garlic powder and tomato juice.
Run at medium speed 1 minute or until mixture is smooth.
Brush chicken with tomato-herb mixture.
Roast chicken at 375° (moderate oven) 2 hours and 20 minutes or until chicken is cooked throughout (drumstick moves easily).
Serve garnished with parsley.
Remove skin.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Arrange potatoes and 1 tablespoon onion evenly in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and parsley flakes.

title: haley's pork chops
directions: Place pork chops on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. In saucepan, slowly cook until tender the water, onion, celery and butter. Put bread cubes in a large bowl. Add onion and water mixture. Mix well. Add salt, pepper, sage and poultry seasoning to your taste. Put stuffing over pork chops. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: In a bowl combine the mandarin orange sections, pineapple chunks, coconut, marshmallows and sour cream.
Cover and chill for several hours or overnight.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies(yields 100 cookies)
directions: Mix fat, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and eggs at medium speed until well blended.
Beat in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt at low speed until well blended.
Stir in peanuts at low speed.
Using No. 40 scoop (1 3/5 tablespoons), drop onto 2 ungreased pans (about 18 x 26 x 1-inch).
Drop 2-inches apart. Bake at 375° (moderate oven) for 12 minutes or until brown.
Cool for 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: old fashioned jam cake
directions: Soak raisins in pineapple overnight.
Sift dry ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl, cream butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add jam and buttermilk; blend well.
Add dry ingredients; mix just until all ingredients are combined. Stir in raisins, pineapple and nuts.
Spread into two greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool completely and ice with Caramel Icing.

title: skillet eggplant
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon margarine in skillet.
Mix well other ingredients.
Simmer covered until eggplant is tender about 20 minutes.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and syrup.
Stir constantly until boiling.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Cool.

title: littlenecks steamed in garlic and oil
directions: Rinse clams in cold water. In a large steaming pot, preheat olive oil and saute onions and garlic for 60 seconds. Add water/wine, clams and season to taste. Cover and steam on high; heat until clams open (6 to 10 minutes). Serve with melted butter and broth.

title: healthy crunchy zucchini sticks
directions: Cut each zucchini lengthwise into fourths, then lengthwise into halves to form sticks.
Cut each stick lengthwise into halves (each zucchini makes 16 sticks).

title: spiced fruit punch
directions: Boil all but oranges.
Strain.
Serve cold or hot with oranges as a garnish.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Cube eggplant; soak in salt water, drain and drop in boiling water.
Cook until tender.
Arrange in layers in buttered baking dish. Dot with butter and pour soup over top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, sugar and cheese.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: savory potato skins
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out potatoes to within 1/4-inch of shell.
(Use for mashed potatoes.)
Cut shells in half again.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, garlic and paprika.
Broil until golden brown, about 5 minutes.

title: chicken breast scampi
directions: Cut raw, boneless chicken breasts into approximately 2 ounces chunks and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, then pour the mixture over the chicken pieces. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Separate chicken pieces and cook for another 10 minutes.
Place chicken under broiler to brown for 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve over rice or thin spaghetti.

title: fried mushroom sandwich
directions: Slice mushrooms.
Beat eggs until dead.
Dip mushrooms in egg batter, then in flour.
Fry in iron skillet with oleo.
Makes a great sandwich.

title: sally o'brien's peach dumplings
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, milk and salt.
Roll dough thin.
Put sliced peaches in center and fold like rectangle.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and cook 10 minutes, possibly 15.
Bake in a pan at 350° or 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: golden pound cake
directions: In medium bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt and mace; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternately with small amounts of evaporated milk, beating well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden skewer comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Dust with sifted powdered sugar.

title: catfish and wild rice soup
directions: Rinse rice and drain.
In medium saucepan, bring water and salt to boil.
Add rice.
Return to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 45 to 55 minutes or until rice is tender.
Drain. Meanwhile, in large kettle, cook onion, celery, garlic and butter until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth, salt, curry powder and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Add catfish.
Return to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in cooked rice, light cream, sherry (if desired) and ground red pepper. Heat through.
Garnish each serving with a lemon slice and parsley sprig.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes and cool.
Mix together cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Hidden Valley Ranch and spread over cooled crescent rolls.
Cut up fine the broccoli, tomato, green pepper, cauliflower and enough onion to taste.
Press into cream cheese mix.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cover and cool for 1 1/2
hours.

title: chicken bake
directions: Roll boneless chicken breasts in sour cream until coated. Crush potato chips and roll coated chicken in chips.
Place chicken in a greased, flat baking dish.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine per breast and drizzle over chicken. Sprinkle top of each breast with garlic powder.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: persimmon fudge
directions: Grease inside of pan.
Cook to soft ball stage; then add 7 ounces of marshmallow cream and 1 cup chopped nuts (your choice). Pour into your greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: southern potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; rinse in cold water.
Put in saucepan and cover with cold water and cook until tender.
Drain and let cool.
Boil eggs to hard-boiled stage.
Peel and chop.
Chop celery and onion.
When potatoes are cool, mix celery, eggs and onion with them.
Add vinegar to mixture or to taste.
Mix well. Add mayonnaise and prepared mustard (more mayonnaise and mustard may be required according to taste).
Refrigerate about 1 hour before serving.
It is better made the day before serving.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Combine butter and sugars.
Blend cinnamon and nutmeg in ice cream.
Mix together.
Freeze.
To each cup of boiling water, add one jigger dark rum, a cinnamon stick and 1 heaping tablespoonful batter.

title: fruit slice cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
To one part, work in
few drops yellow food color and the lemon peel.
To another part, work in green food color and lime peel.
To another, work in orange food color and orange peel.
Leave remaining part plain.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Mix broth, chicken and soup together and pour in casserole dish.
Mix margarine, flour and milk together and spoon over chicken.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: ham loaf
directions: Pour over loaf.
Baste often.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Bring to boil first 5 ingredients.
Add rice; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add broccoli; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Transfer to blender or food processor and puree.
Return to saucepan; add milk, salt and cayenne.
Serve hot or refrigerate and serve cold.
You may top each serving with a spoonful of low-fat sour cream and chopped chives, dill or parsley.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes with skin on.
Put enough water in pan to boil amount of potatoes you are cooking.
Dissolve 5 to 6 bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Place whole potatoes in water.
Cook until almost done (do not overcook).
When potatoes are almost done, prepare skillet with 1/2 amount of oil and 1/2 amount of margarine (just enough to fry potatoes).
Cut potatoes in about 2-inch cubes and place in hot skillet.
Season with seasoned salt, garlic powder and parsley flakes.
(Season to your own taste.) Fry potatoes until golden brown.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Brown ground round in skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese, and cook about 30 minutes.
Add cheese and let melt.
Serve with cornbread.

title: strawberry cool 'n easy pie
directions: In a large bowl, completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Mix cold water and ice to measure 3/4 cup.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in whipped Cool Whip with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 15-20 minutes or until mixture is very thick and will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Top with strawberry slices.
Makes 8 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In bowl, whisk together sour cream, milk, Butter Buds, cornstarch and pepper.
Spray pan with vegetable oil spray. Slice potatoes 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Place 1/2 potatoes in pan. Cover with 1/2 sour cream mixture.
Put 1/2 onions on top.
Place the rest of potatoes, sour cream mixture and onions.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and continue baking for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast marmalade
directions: Wash fruit and slice into paper-thin strips.
Put the seeds in a little cheesecloth bag.
Measure fruit and for every cupful, add 2 cups of water.
Put seeds in for more flavor.
Let stand 24 hours.
Remove seeds; cook fruit until tender and let stand until cool.
Now measure fruit and add an equal amount of sugar.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Pour into sterile jars at once.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Boil hen that has been seasoned.
Debone.
Bake according to instructions the cornbread.
Crumble into chicken broth and soup and rice.
Saute green onions (tops and all) and onion in margarine.
Add seasonings.
Place in cornbread mixture along with toasted bread and eggs and deboned chicken.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in appropriate pan and cook.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
In mixing bowl, prepare muffin mix as per package instructions.
Add both cans of corn, sour cream and butter.
Stir to mix and add back to greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken soup
directions: Divide the chicken into pieces at joints.
Add to the water with ham, garlic, onion and salt.
Let stand for half an hour. Place over the heat until the chicken is tender.
Strain.
Add potatoes, vermicelli and chicken pieces.
Cook until the potatoes are done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, stir soup and soy sauce until smooth; mix in 1/2 can onions, beans and pepper.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbling.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.
Please double recipe.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and stir to coat.
Continue to stir until coating is absorbed by crackers.

title: easy eggplant
directions: Place bacon in a 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Cover with wax paper; microwave at High for 5 to 7 minutes, or until crisp. Remove bacon, reserving drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Add eggplant, green pepper, celery, onion and water; stir well.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap (do not vent).
Microwave vegetables at High for 6 minutes, giving dish a quarter turn at 2-minute intervals.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain.
Add tomatoes, brown sugar, salt and pepper to eggplant mixture; stir well.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap; microwave at High for 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bacon.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: crab spread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a small ovenproof baking dish. Mash the cream cheese and milk until creamy and blend in the onion, crabmeat and horseradish, mixing well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on crackers or party rye bread.

title: sausage cake
directions: Dissolve soda in a little cold water.
Break up sausage in mixing bowl.
Add sugar and raisins (or dates).
Pour boiling water over all mixture.
Stir in soda water.
Sift other ingredients together.
Add to contents of bowl.
Stir in nuts. Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
May bake in an iron cake mold between 250° and 275° for about 2 hours or until done.

title: apple cake with vanilla pudding(eplekake med vanilje pudding)
directions: Cook your favorite vanilla pudding and let it cool.
Grease a 9 x 1 1/2-inch spring-form pan.
Blend flour, sugar and margarine and mix as for a pie crust.
Divide dough; take 2/3 and press on bottom and sides of the pan.
Peel 4 big apples and slice; arrange them in the pan.
Pour cooled pudding over the apples.
Roll out the rest of the dough and cover the cake.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt margarine in bowl in microwave.
Stir in flour to paste. Slowly mix milk with paste, then microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High, stopping to stir every minute.
(Should be smooth and thickened). Salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry pie (just like shoney's)
directions: Boil for 1 minute and cool.
Arrange 1 pint fresh sliced strawberries into a cooked pie shell and cover with boiled mixture.

title: old fashioned never fail egg custard
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well. Add margarine, milk and flavoring.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes in 450° oven.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until silver knife comes out clean when inserted in middle of pie.

title: sparkling fruit punch
directions: In a large bowl, combine lemonade and pineapple with water and grenadine syrup.
Just before serving, add grape juice and ginger ale.
Stir to blend.
Float ice ring in punch bowl.
Makes 24 (1/2 cup) servings.
Very good.

title: basic fudge
directions: Combine the first four ingredients in a saucepan and stir constantly.
Add the next four ingredients and boil 9 minutes.
Be sure to stir constantly or it will scorch your pan.
Yield:
4 pounds.

title: simple simon souffle
directions: Cook sausage.
Add spinach; cook until done.
Drain.
Mix the cream cheese with a little milk to make smooth.
Put all eggs in bowl and beat.
Add cream cheese, sausage and spinach; mix well. Pour into souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: sliced turkey with cranberry salsa
directions: Combine tomatoes, cranberry sauce, green onion, jalapeno pepper, lime juice, sugar, salt and pepper in medium-size bowl. Transfer half of the mixture to the container of a food processor. Pulse with on-off motion until mixture reaches the consistency of a thick sauce.
Add sauce in blender back to mixture in bowl. Stir to combine.
Refrigerate, covered, until ready to serve.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can be used right away, but it is better if it is refrigerated overnight.

title: sugar pie
directions: Combine flour and sugar and mix well.
Add boiling water. When smooth, add lump of butter.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: sweet and tart salad
directions: Mix cabbage and apples together.

title: chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over chicken and apple, mixing lightly. Combine mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add olives and celery and mix. Then toss this mixture with chicken and apples.
Serve cold on lettuce leaf.

title: peach cobbler
directions: *Melt margarine in 10 x 14 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: quick chili con queso
directions: Melt cheese with the milk in a microwave bowl in the microwave until the cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
After the cheese is melted, stir in the salsa or the tomatoes and chilies; mix well.
Heat in microwave again, if necessary.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mikhail's roast peppers and anchovies
directions: This is a simple appetizer which can be prepared immediately before serving or refrigerated after cooking and served (hot or cold) at a later date.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger in large kettle; add the water, seasonings and tomatoes (mashed).
Simmer slowly 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with a big pan of cornbread and lots of cold milk; put some bright jelly on the table to spread on corn bread.
(Makes a good meal.)

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in buttered dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lunchmeat pizza
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough. Cut in half. Roll out half of the bread and place in 1 1/2 to 2-inch deep baking dish. Spread with spaghetti sauce. Layer lunch meats and cheese. Roll out other half of bread. Place on top and seal edge. Bake at 350° until bread is browned and sounds hollow when tapped.
Best when served cold.

title: old-fashioned taffy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in a 4-quart saucepan and place over medium heat.
Do not stir.
Cook until mixture reaches soft ball stage.

title: butterscotch tapioca cream
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 1/4 cup packed brown sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time until soft peaks form.
Set aside.
Melt butter; add 2/3 cup brown sugar and cook until dissolved.
In another pan, mix yolks, milk, tapioca and salt.
Cook until mix comes to a full boil.
Add butterscotch mixture and mix well. Pour a little in meringue, blending well.
Quickly stir in remaining mixture.
Add vanilla and let stand for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir.
Serve warm or cold.

title: spinach surprise
directions: Cook the spinach with the onion.
Melt the butter; add the spinach, well drained, and stir it.
Then add the salt and sour cream or yogurt and blend it together.
Finally, stir in the vinegar and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream chicken breasts
directions: Roll chicken in flour flavored with salt and pepper.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Roll in seasoned bread crumbs and place in shallow baking dish.
Spread mushrooms over top of chicken.
Mix chicken bouillon, mushroom soup and sour cream in a bowl, then pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 400° until it stops bubbling and starts to brown, then cut back to 300° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon party cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1/2 cup dry cake mix.
In large mixer bowl, combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil; mix well (mixture will be crumbly).
Press firmly on bottom and 1 1/2 inches up sides of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In same bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add remaining 3 eggs and reserved 1/2 cup cake mix; on medium speed, beat 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill thoroughly. Cut into squares to serve.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add flour and pecans; mix well.
Add bananas.
Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: depression cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and sugar or honey.
Cut bacon grease into dry ingredients.
Add raisin juice and raisins; stir.
Batter will be very thick.

title: shrimp-cheese spread
directions: Place shrimp and onion in blender and blend thoroughly. Combine remaining ingredients and chill.

title: crab dip(blue label)
directions: The more mayonnaise that you use the better and creamier.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash, onion and margarine together until tender.
Add squash mixture to crumbs and soup.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: macaroni with mixed vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables and macaroni separately according to package directions; drain.
Combine milk and soup in saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and heated through.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Parboil eggplant for 20 minutes.
Remove to platter to cool. Slice lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving the shell of eggplant. Chop up all ingredients fine.
Mix well.
Put back in shell of eggplant.
Top with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Mix cake mix and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan, reserving 1/2 cup of mixture.
Heat Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter until blended, stirring constantly.
Spread cream mixture over cake mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: old-fashioned hot fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, measure chocolate, Bisquick, milk, vanilla and 2/3 cup sugar.
With wire whisk, beat ingredients until smooth.
Pour batter into 9 x 12-inch pan.
In small bowl, mix cocoa and 1/3 cup sugar.
Sprinkle over batter in pan.
Carefully pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over all.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake 25 minutes.
(Batter will separate into cake and fudge sauce after baking.)
Serve immediately.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in top of double boiler.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour melted butter and marshmallows over ingredients and mix well.
Shape into loaf or roll.
Wrap in wax paper and aluminum foil and store in refrigerator.

title: frozen slaw(makes approximately 10 cups)
directions: Put cabbage into colander and drain 1 to 2 hours.
Chop green pepper and carrots and set side.

title: punch
directions: Boil the sugar and water together for 8 minutes.
Add tea and chill.
Add the juice of the oranges and lemons, grape juice and the pineapple.
Place in the refrigerator for 2 hours.
Before serving add ginger ale and ice cubes.
